messages: ["Arrivederci my friend to the south. Could we agree on a dmz in tyrolia? I've already contacted Austria about it and am waiting on a response", 'How are you thinking of moving to open up the game and are you open to any ideas?', "Hi Germany, I'm down with the DMZ - Have you heard back from Austria yet?", 'Yes. He seemed to be in agreement. Who are you looking to move on to open up?', 'Just checking in again. Who are you looking to move on? Might you be interested in working together against France? I could help you solidify quite a good bit of Mediterranean', "I'm not sure if I'm not getting my messages or something or if you're not getting mine. Just lmk", 'sorry been out and about. Definitely not a fan of the French spread - Do you have anything specific in mind?', 'I figured Marseilles and at least part of Iberia would go to you. Give me a sec to look at the map']

messages: ['Hi Austria, what are your thoughts on Tyr? Any ideas for opening moves more generally?', "I'd like to see Tyr remain a DMZ as not to provoke any hostilies between myself, you or Germany. Thoughts?", 'Works for me! Are you looking to expand into the Balkans first? Would you be interested in Italy-Austria alliance to take on Turkey there?', "I believe conflict between Russia and Turkey is inevitable so I plan to wait and see what happens there. I'd appreciate support in the future should it come to it, and rest assured that I will endeavour to help you should you be attacked", 'Keeping Russia out of Rum, nice. How deep does this alliance with Turkey run?', "We're on good terms and it seems to be working out for both of us thus far\n\nHow are you with Germany and France?", 'How would you feel about moving out of Greece and taking Tunisia instead?', "what's in it for me?", "I'd like to hold it for at least one more season, but then will probably move out", "What happened to Tyr being a DMZ, and what happened with Greece? I'm willing to give you the benefit of the doubt as I've cocked up with convoys many times", 'Turns out drunk orders are bad orders', 'What are you planning doing this turn?', 'Turning on France to the east', "Not sure I like how powerful you're letting Turkey get though...", 'Now that the Turks have stabbed you in the back, would you be willing to support my fleet Apulian-Ionian?', 'Consider it done', 'Thanks, much appreciated - Hoping to work together more going forward!']

messages: ['Hi Italy! A Russian Italian alliance can be a very powerful thing mid game. What do you think? We could just stay in good contact until the time comes and then work together even more', "So ig I'm just suggesting that we stay friends until mid game where we contact one another and could have a very powerful alliance.", 'How is your relationship with austria?', "Long term relationship sounds good to me, if only so that I can honor our overlord administrator's motherland", 'Hi Russia, I', "Re Austria, we've reached a truce on Tyr for now, but think they're two-timing me with Turkey for the Balkans", "idk if it's true just letting u know since were allies", 'Germany(who says is allied with Austria) is telling me that they are planning on attacking you', 'Appreciate the heads up also', "Ok italy! It's time. W/ the Austrian turkey alliance, I propose we work together to take them out", 'Agree, Turkey did me dirty there', 'Yep', 'Could you attempt to take Venice?', 'lol wut', 'Sorry I meant the country next to Venice that Austria has and I’m to lazy to remebwrb', 'Thanks for taking Tyr. We should be able to punish Austria this turn/', 'I think a move to Eas has a lot of potentiall', "I don't think that's feasible with the Turkish fleets at the moment", 'what are your dealings with Germany and Austria like?', 'Which direction are you looking to head this turn?', "I'm trying to make an alliance with turkey., so maybe move in on Austria .Germany and me are at war. Germany will fall soon with the pressure from me and France. Feel free to join us in Tyr.", 'Trying to work on an alliance with turkey. Are you on board for going against Austria?', 'Could you maybe have ion support aeg to gre? I’m trying to work with turkey and we are both interested to get you in this so we can give Austria a quick end.', "I'm game to play but only if I'm the one getting supported into Greece", 'Concerned  about a giant Turkey', 'Can you talk to turkey about that’s', 'Ok', "Also why can't Turkey just take Gre itself?", 'Heads up, planning on moving into Tyr - Can support against Boh next season']

messages: ['Hello dearest Italy. How goes things in your section of Europe?', 'Turning my attention to Greece for now, but would be interested in a long-term strategy against France!', 'Hello Italy!', "I'd like to discuss the Franco-German conflict with you", 'Italy? If you are available I have an offer for you.', 'I am listening!', 'So as you likely see, Germany and France have a bit of a spat going on right now. Should the situation devolve to naval attacks against my own territory, would you be willing to exchange French/German lands in the south for your involvement/', '?*', 'My northern neighbors, how goes it?', 'How are your relations with Russia and France?', 'Hello dearest Italy, I have reasonably close relations with my fellow northerners']

messages: ["Hey Italy, how's things? I'm hoping that we can build a good relationship in this one. Have you heard from Austria?", "Hey Turkey, Austria floated the idea of joint expansion into the Balkans. I'm not super interested in heading that way so not planning on supporting them", 'Hmm ok they also told me that they wanted to keep you out of Greece so they lied to either you or I or I guess something has changed their mind.', 'Looks like Russia is firmly committed South but Germany is gifting them Sweden plus England looks like they wont put up any resistance either. A runaway Russia looks likely. Do you plan to try for Greece?', "Only if you'd be willing to support - I'd hold it as the edge of my western expansion, but have no interest in going further. Do you know where Austria plans to go? Turkey-Italy alliance could push Austria north to face Germany and Russia.", "Yeah fair enough. I can't be sure of what Austria plans to do now as they seem to be spreading misinformation pretty liberally according to Russia. I will let you know if I'm in a position to support you into Greece. May need to try and keep Russia out of Rum. Would be more than happy to work together - I have no faith in what either Russia or Austria are telling me.", 'Nice work in Rum! How deep does that Austria alliance run though?', 'If you were to attack Ser, I would support', 'You still planning to leave Greece?', 'Yes, getting out this season.', 'Would you be able to support me into Gre?', 'I cant support you into Greece, but I can support you into TRI in the fall', 'But first you need to retreat to NAP not ALB. Hope that works for you.', 'ok sounds good']

messages:
['What are your thoughts on Piedmont?', 'Bonjour, happy to keep it a dmz for now.', "Sounds great, let's do that then.", 'France, what are you thinking about for your open?', "I'm not 100% sure but I do think I will be playing some safe moves", 'Thanks for keeping the DMZ in Piedmont', 'Any news regarding what may be happening with Austria or Turkey?', 'England went to the English Channel so I just wanted to give you a heads up that I am looking to build a second fleet in Marseilles that is NOT headed towards you', 'It would be really bad did Austria built an army in Trieste and supported it into Venice', 'You might want to consider an army in Rome if you are worried about that', 'Appreciate the heads up re Mar', "Turkey-Austria alliance cuts me deep but hopefully isn't too long-term", 'Any idea what England and Germany are up to?  Who are you closer with?', 'I think Germany plans to retake Munich. No idea what England plans to do with the channel.', 'Turkey said he plans to flip sides and pursue a Russia Turkey alliance. I would definitely watch out for that', 'Interesting, Turkey and I are going to team up against Austria.', 'Cool. I do worry about Turkey getting so large. He seems to be very manipulative.', 'FYI, moving into Tyr - Not trying to cause trouble, just trying to get better position on Austria', "If you aren't doing anything with Tyrolia, can it support Ruhr to Munich?", 'I just looked closer at the moves. Darn, was the fleet in Rome supposed to be an army?', 'Turkey looks pretty aggressive and is positioned to take both Greece and Sevastopol this turn', 'Any new thoughts on moves?', 'Do you have any Intel on Germany or England by any chance?', "Are we still good? I'm not sure what your silence means.", 'Hey France, sorry was offline for most of Labor Day weekend!', 'No worries', 'I hope you got your moves figured out- not sure if you got my previous messages but if you are still around it would be nice to check in quickly', "We should talk about moves. I think it's vital that we work together against Turkey and so I'm hoping I might be able to help you with my fleet", "I would love to see you inTyrolia again. I'm trying to take Munich back", 'We should definitely talk since Turkey just built a second fleet', 'It would be a good idea I think to take the Adriatic and the Ionian, and I can be a third fleet to help you keep the Ionian.', "I'm extremely worried about an Austria-Turkey alliance dominating the board, and a Turkey solo resulting from it. Adriatic will keep Venice safe for a very long time and also serve as a way to defend the Ionian. My fleet can also help with the defense if you so request.", "Agree - Trying to figure out how deep Austria's alliance runs. Think Turkey will have to swallow it sooner than later, so hoping to turn them to help contain", 'Sounds good. I can tell you that the alliance is rock solid right now, and they probably will stay allies the whole game unless they get stuck', 'It looks like Austria was already trying to get into position to attack you since you bounced with them in the Adriatic Sea', 'Hmm. I wonder if it makes sense to support Ionian to hold this time since Turkey is in the Eastern Mediterranean. Austria might be worried about Venice-Trieste and not go to the Adriatic again', 'If you think that Turkey will stab Austria you could also ask him to support your convoy into Greeve', 'This is just a suggestion. But something to consider:
Ionian Sea C Tunis-Albania
Tunis-Albania
Venice-Trieste
Tyrhenian Sea S Ionian Sea H', 'Turkey can just take Gre on its own', 'Damn. You would have been in such a strong position if you used the suggestion I gave you!', 'You would have taken Trieste for a build, you would have kept control of the Ionian Sea, andd you would have an army in Albania to take Serbia or Greece.', "I'm on your side- I'm trying g to help you. Iyou are prudent to distrust me, but it's us Vs Turkey and Austria right now. I'm trying to prevent a Turkish solo!", 'If I were you, I would retreat to Apulia', 'This is the only way to prevent Austria from taking the Adriatic for free. It also lets me help you with my fleet if you move Tyrhenian to Naples and my fleet moves to the Tyrhenian', "Anyway, we're still in a great place due to some lucky guesses by Russia and Germany NMRing, so I'm going to help you as much as I can. Just ask.", 'Would you be ok with me building an army in Marseilles? This would give me the option of moving to Piedmont with the goal of taking Tyrolia and helping you attack Austria', 'Have you tried sending messages to me? If so, I am not receiving them.', "That could be the case if you don't mark the message with the thumbs up or thumbs down.", 'I highly recommend that you move to Apulia to prevent Turkey from convoying a unit into that territory.', 'Truly the hindsight is 20/20', "Yeah, that's one of the frustrating things about Diplomacy haha. Glad you are here- I'm moving to the Tyrhenian and to Piedmont right now to help out.", 'Awesome moves this turn! What do you want me to do with Piedmont and Tyrhenian Sea? Any ideas for me?', 'Not sure what your plan is, but I might be able to support you to Munich.', 'Any thoughts on moves?', "I don't know what you are doing, but for now I am supporting Apulia-Ionian Sea and Piedmont-Tyrolia", "That's perfect and much appreciated!!", 'How are your relations with England right now?', 'Hmm, I would say they are pretty tense, but still cordial.', 'Sorry for changing the plan- I desperately needed the builds to have even a small chance of attacking England- just wanted to say that I have absolutely nothing else to gain from attacking you', 'Your only threat at this point is Turkey, so If you keep Naples and the Ionian you will never lose Tunis or Naples and have a strong chance to pick up Greece', 'If you keep the armies I think Turkey would get Tunis and Naples, and you would be eliminated and therefore not get paid the survivor prize pool money.', 'Vienna is open if you move there', "I totally understand if you do- but I hope you don't bounce me out of the Tyrhenian Sea again so that I can counter Turkey", "You have every right to throw all your unts against me- but I hope we don't have to go that route"]

messages: ['Hello neighbor. We have quite an historic relationship. I hope we can keep the peace. Dmz tyrolia?', 'Greetings my Germanic Brethren! Keeping the peace is definitely at the forefront of my foreign policy. Making Tyrol a DMZ sounds perfectly reasonable to me', 'Excellent! :)', 'Any further action you might want to take together?', 'Probably best to just stay on alert at the moment and respond to any threats as they arise', 'Yeah sounds like a good plan :)', "Seems like you're playing it slow. I'm not sure if you've talked to turkey, but I think you've got a golden opportunity to move with him on Russia. What you do afterwards is your business", 'Not to cast aspersions, but what will you be doing should I move my forces to attack Russia?', "Ohhhh haha no I'm not looking to move on you. I moved all my troops that opposite way. I think it's genuinely good for you (especially with Italy starting a Lepanto) and if Russia is busy it frees me up in the west. You see what I'm saying?", "I did think that was your reasoning, but one can't be too careful! 😂", 'Is there any chance you could disrupt SIL for me this turn, or are you too caught up with the French and English?']

messages: ["Hello czar :) I think we should discuss a few things. A dmz of Silesia and Prussia would benefit us both. Let me know what you think. Also, there are plenty of joint risks to us both, particularly as the game progresses. Let me know if you've got any interest working together", "Hm I'm getting your messages only in email form. Not to worry. Yes, I did say Prussia in my original message. I think the Baltic sea sounds fair enough as well. Why don't we work together toward those ends? I'm not shocked at the idea Britain might be looking to come for me", "Hi germany! Are you up for Sil as a DMZ? It would be in both of our best interests if we didn't get in a fight early on, as both of our great powers already have a lot to deal with on our sides of the map. Looking forwards to a great game!\n\n-Russia", "A DMZ of Prussia and the Baltic might also not hurt. And if you're up to it, maybe even a potential alliance against England?", 'I have heard some murmers of England wanting to attack you.', 'Also looking forward to a great game and a great alliance if we could hash something out :) did you get my earlier message in response to your last two messages I received by email', 'I did. Are you thinking of forging an alliance with France? If so that would be great since me and France are already on really good terms.', 'Have you gotten my messages?', "Yes, sorry. Been a bit busy. Well, you say messages. Before the. Message asking if I got your messages (plural) I received one about allying with France. Him and I definitely seem to be on good terms and I'm not looking for war with him. If we can work something out, I would love to be able to work with him.", 'That would be great. Me and France are and you could be powerful allies, especially later in the game', 'I think France is being friendly with everyone', "I can't say ik certain of how things will go in the west but I like to maintain peace as long as possible and a few allies I can trust is important as hell in this game", 'I think so too... Thoughts on that?', 'Well they are probably pretending to be friends with everyone and then they will betray one or two...', 'What’s your relationship like with England?', "Yeah. It's hard to trust him and he seems to be posturing for a move on Munich", "I've been talking with England. I'm not really sure if it's positive or negative or if I trust him quite yet. Why do you ask?", "had a sorta anti-russian opening and just seeing who's on who's side", "I'm w/ Austria against turkey", "Somewhat, but to be fair that's also a very common English open. I don't know if I if he's looking to make an attack and I'd be on my toes if I were you but I don't think it's anything catastrophic", 'I think that has an awful lot of potential for success. Best of luck in the south mate :)', 'Thanks. Good luck to you too!', 'Thanks for sharing! Good luck over there in the west!', "If you're interested, you could send some units over to the balkans and me/italy/you could try to take out Russia and Austria as they are allied now", "I don't completely understand the ask", 'Also why are you moving on me man?', 'Have you given up?]']

messages: ["I messaged you on backstabbr then I realized I don't think I'm supposed to do that 🤷\u200d♂️", "So, basic gist was I think we have a lot of opportunity to work together and common interests, if you're open to it", 'I am inclined to agree. How would you like to approach Scandinavia?', "I'd like denmark, norways all yours. Perhaps we could move on Russia but I think we should start with france, otherwise he'll become a problem for us both. After that we can hash out the rest of scandanavia and Russia as it goes?", 'Alright. Are we content to let Russia take Sweden with no contest?', "If we put up a fight we'll have to go for Russia right away. If we did that, what would we do about France", "That's fair. I'm personally pro-leave Sweden to Russia but I wanted to double-check with you.", 'What would you like to do against France?', "Alright. We'll leave it for now. I was hoping to get you into brest as soon as possible and then me into Paris and then decide from there? Likely you in Iberia and me in Marseilles but I don't want to count our chickens before they're hatched", 'Alright sounds good.', "Hey what's the deal with France? They're talking about an alliance between us three to counter Russia and Italy?", "He hasn't told me about that. An EFGs an interesting proposition... But idk. What do you think? And wdu mean what's his deal?", 'How do you want to open up? There are a lot of options and opportunities?', 'But he may just have figured we want to move west and tried to throw me off', 'I ask because he said he already talked to you about it.', "I think I'm going to go EC to be aggressive on France, and take Norway", "He also said he's working closely w france", "Let's be aggressive with france so we can switch back to Russia asap", 'Hm yeah Russia also told me there were murmurs you wanted to attack me', "My only dialogue with Russia has been to advocate for the equal sharing of Scandinavia. I've been told that Russia seems to want to commit south.", 'I suspect that France and Russia are both worried about two players moving on them early, and may be in an alliance to stretch us out.', "If Russia DOES want to commit south, it is logical that they'd try to prevent a united northern threat. Considering that Rus/Fr may be coordinating, I am going to play cautiously  and refrain from committing east or west", "Russia admitted to me that he's in an alliance with france", "He intends to move on you it seems, so I don't think he's truly committing south. Maybe just maintaining a hold. Either way time will tell", "You told me you were looking to move aggressively against France. If we can get Russia distracted by turkey especially with Austrian help ik the south their alliance won't matter", "I was gonna play aggressive but i'm going to slow down to protect my expansion. I don't want to deprive myself of builds because I spread myself too thin", "I'm gonna to move to secure Norway, and maybe place myself to support you in Benelux or move against France next turn", "If Fr's fleet moves to secure Spain I'll go in", "Alright. Sounds fine with me. Just let me know of your intentions going forward so I don't end up acting alone. Seems like Russia is focused on the south which is excellent news for a move on France if we could just get Austria involved. He's playing awfully passive", 'What happened with the Liverpool to London misorder last turn?', 'Regarding France, are you trying to take Belgium? I would prefer to have it because otherwise you can get 3 builds and myself only 1', 'it works on the website I normally play', "I'm not sure. I was under the impression I could move an army into a space that was becoming vacant", "oh I realize now that I'm a fool and it doesnt border. I wasnt paying attention putting down the move", "Lol yeah they don't border 😂", "And I hate to be so greedy to open up but I'm nervous that if I forego a build it opens me up to have Russia, France or both collapse on me and then we're really fucked. Particularly if France walks into Munich, I'll need both builds badly", "I'm more than willing to cede territory to you going forward when I'm better in a position to subdue France or Russia depending on what we've decided. Does that sound alright?", "It's really funny that you mention France and Munich.", "It just so happens that I've been talking to France, and they're under the impression that I'll bounce you out of Denmark if they march into Munich.", "Ah so he is moving into Munich? While I'd rather have that scenario not happen", 'He may very well test my loyalty and let me try to bounce out of Denmark first, but he offered to march to Munich if I bounced you', 'Btw have you talked to Italy?', "(my last message doesn't look to have sent correctly so I'll repeat)", 'Have you talked to Italy? They might be helpful soon', "Anywho I'm gonna try to tie up the French fleet and take Norway. We can talk about territory later", 'Well how would you like to work this one out?', "And he hadn't responded in a while. Just messaged him again", 'Alright so how are you looking to move and are you fine letting me have the three builds?', "I'm going Nor and EC. You can have your  3 builds rn, but I'll be expecting land later since you're getting two builds on me", 'Also if France asks you about an alliance, we definitely had a convo about a loose 3 way alliance', "Alright excellent. Sounds good. We'll even it out. Promise that. I just want a healthy border around my home centers and a guarantee I can push back France", 'Oh OK. So you and I had a convo about a loose efg?', 'Yeah. Just in case France tries to check', 'Right makes sense', "But he attacked me so I'm moving in", 'Alright that sounds good. Do you want me to move into Brest?', 'Also what should I go about building?', 'Go for it although hell probably build a fleet there', 'Oh sorry missed this', "You built a fleet in Edinburgh? Why? I'd think you'd want it in London no?", 'Yeah I was thinking London for a long time but I reached the conclusion that i would feel better with a fleet that could serve as a sort of home fleet, and I figured London served as a better base for attacks', "I'm not sure yet if its a good plan, but I figured no harming in trying it out", "I suppose so but Russia isn't gonna be able to come your way and we're supposed to be attack France rn so...", "Alright can we renegotiate? I'm not sure what France said to sway you. Was it the three initial builds? Cuz you can have Belgium. I'd just really prefer to knock out France. Belgium brest and Portugal can be yours. All I want is Paris and Italy can take Marseilles and Spain. Really we can really negotiate however I'd just rather not be at odds w you. Now I'd figure you'd much rather ally w me seeing as France has struck a deal w every nation I've talked to so far which makes him not that trustworthy and he has three fleets that can easily slip in your back door to my one that you have pinned on land... So if you head my way he's gonna walk in your back door. I would bet you money. What do you say? Can we strike some sort of deal?", 'Le me know your thoughts', "I'm sorry mate. France's fleets are too big for me to piss him off. I won't push past Denmark, and if you can negotiate peace with him I'll respect it", 'Alright. Understood', "I mean honestly mate he's gonna attack you either way. And the two of us can stop him... I'm not sure why you'd back off like that. I don't mean to be rude but how much experience do you have with this game?", "I'm saying honestly both cuz it's by far the most logical thing to do and he's in great position to do it now that he's advanced and you've completely backed off and cuz it's literally what he told me he was going to do", 'What makes you say we can push him back if he has deals with everyone?', "If you surrender Denmark to me, I will help you survive France's push. I am not going to involve myself in this war for either side without immediately tangible benefits. France is a difficult invasion for me, and I've spent a lot of time in the North Sea with no new land.", "He doesn't have actual deals. Not ones people are intending to follow through on cuz they don't trust him cuz he makes deals w everyone. Russia doesn't trust him and is way too busy w Austria and turkey. Italy doesn't trust him either and I convinced him to invade the south although he's kind of a mess at the moment. I actually don't know if turkey or Austria has any sort of deal with france. And who is actually free to intervene against us?", "I'm not sure how you can make tangible benefits if you don't involve yourself though honestly. And if you help me out we'll topple France and how can I come attack you? Honestly. France is headed for you as we speak and is trying to sue for peace with me so that he can complete his invasion of you. Not to mention he has three fleets you just turned your back on. Please, listen to reason here. Either way, I'd much rather you take Belgium. Can we make that deal?", "Sorry about the delay. I'm willing to exchange Belgium for cooperation against France.", 'Alright sounds good', "How should I move? I don't know how to handle his fleets", 'Well moving out of the channel seriously set you back', 'But we can fix this', 'If you move to the north Atlantic, English Channel and North sea and your army to Wales you can cover your back side and set up a convoy route into France', "How's that sound", 'I am not gonna go Nor Atl bcause I want a fleet in Nor, but the rest sounds good. France wants to move into Picardy this turn', "Also given how weird the western triangle has been, can I ask what you're going to do with your fleet? turning to face france leaves me vulnerable in that regard", "Oh I honestly don't know yet", "But I start the game w it and built two armies so I'm not exactly looking for naval dominance"]

messages: ["We might have some space between us now, but it won't be long until we're on each other's door steps. You want to hash out a long term plan for cooperation?", 'Hello and thanks for your message! I am certainly interested in your ideas on this. Have you heard from Italy or Austria at all yet?', 'Not yet. Have you?', 'Nothing yet either.', 'Alright keep me updated', 'I think Russia is committing south. Do you plan to bounce him out of Sweden?', 'What makes you say that? And no not likely', 'Well he has told me he wants to attack Austria. And Austria has told me that he told them that he wanted to attack me. If either of those are true then a 3 unit south start seems likely.', "Hm understood. I think either way it might be in your best interests to jump on Russia. I can't right away but I can come help you later in the game", 'Yeah, I guess you have France to worry about? Otherwise Warsaw would be a pretty easy option for you.', "Yes this much is true. Once I figure out the west thought I think we're in a great situation to collaborate"]

messages: ["I'm hoping we can come to a few agreements. Burgundy is a trouble spot for us both. Could we dmz it? I think at the worst, non agression would be in both our best interests, but I'd definitely be open to any proposition you've got", "Sorry for the brief message- I'll be available for more negotiation later today. I currently want to support Paris to Burgundy since I am not sure what everyone's plans are yet, and if it looks like we are in good position to work together in the fall I can use Burgundy to take Belgium.", 'No worries. Alright. I understand the move to burgundy but I think it should be obvious that any move into my territory would be met with aggression. Update me in the fall of your intentions?', "Thanks. Yeah, it's not that I don't trust you to DMZ Burgundy, but I can't think of a reason not to make the move honestly since it completely protects me against both you and Italy and still leaves room for us to work together. In that sense it leaves me some flexibility to decide my intentions in the fall- the truth is that I currently have no intentions and will let my targets pick themselves.", 'What are your plans in terms of your moves?', "It looks like we've already got ourselves a rat. I've heard rumors of Britain looking to attack me. Correct me if I'm wrong but I'm sure he's roped you in too. While, on the flipside he keeps trying to convince me to attack you alongside him. I think he wants to pit us against each other and use the opportunity to swoop against either or both of us. I think we should knock him out while we have the opportunity", 'Yeah, I think you could be right about this. What would this look like? Do you think England will end up taking the Channel?', "Has he contacted you? And I'm not sure. I don't think he'd be that aggressive right from the start. I can't say I know for sure. What do you want to do?", 'England did contact me. I might be inclined to take the channel if Russia went to St Petersburg with an army, but at the moment I think it is better to wait and see', '(wait and see in terms of how to attack England)', 'Nice opening moves. Are you going for Belgium? I was planning to head there from Burgundy but it looks like you are in a position to support yourself in anyway.', "Yeah. Like I said seems England wouldn't be so thoroughly aggressive for a first move. But we should keep an eye out you're right", "Thank you. Yeah I'd like to take Belgium. I hope there's no issue with that", 'I am concerned over you getting 3 builds and would be a lot more comfortable with that arrangement if you build 2 fleets', "To be honest I haven't thought about builds. I'll build completely contingent on how everyone around me is postured. If you're not in position and russias not in a position to attack me considering two fleets is a lot more viable", 'Now why would you do that my friend? Bad mistake', "I know it is an aggressive move, and I wanted to tell you about it but I couldn't risk not getting the additional build to put down 2 fleets and attack England", 'I will be withdrawing from Munich immediately if you are willing to help with the assualt- I know what this looks like but I promise you will absolutely love my builds', 'One more point. England proposed a plan to bounce you out of Denmark (but I knew he was lying about it)', "See you could've gotten those two fleet builds with Portugal and Spain. You don't need the army in Paris unless you want to attack me. If you don't build your army in Paris and only build the fleets, we'll be fine. If you build the army in Paris it's going to mean war", 'I can do that for sure, though it does mean slowing down potential convoys into England. What does this look like more broadly? Would you be willing to build a fleet in Kiel to take the North Sea? Does this mean you are letting me keep Munich so I can build a fourth fleet next turn?', 'Also, we can get creative with my unit in Munich by sending it to Tyrolia to attack and/or help Austria', "I want to make this work to the point of potentially waiving a build, so I hope we can figure this out. Completely realistically speaking, I think EG struggles to take out F, and EF or FG has a much easier time just considering the distribution of builds. That's really important in a game that ends in 1910", "Another consideration is that England seems like the type of person to switch sides at a moment's notice, and there are some concerns regarding whether they can write orders without a misorder (given their turn 1 misorder)", "I think that The best way to do that is for you to build F Kiel and A Berlin, which I realize is a tough sell, but if we do that we can have 5 fleets on England's 3 and quickly roll over him", 'No response?', "I couldn't waive a build without hearing anything back from you", 'It was written and I then changed my orders', 'Yeah sorry thought I responded', "I can't really do a fleet build", 'You understand', 'I think we could work together but I definitely need you out of Munich and back to burgundy and then out of burgundy from there', "So let's work something out. What's the game plan?", "Why do you seem so determined to go after me? I have you at a stalemate that only England can break meaning he'll reap the rewards and Italy and England are both poorly defended. I honestly just want to know the strategic motivation behind it. Legitimate question. I'm curious what you see that I don't...", "I'll send Brest to English Channel and MAO to Irish Sea, but I need Belgium so that I don't go down a build.", "In regards to your question, wouldn't you agree that it is not me, but you who are committed towards attacking me? You built two armies and tried to take Picardy. Not saying we can't recover from that- but you left yourself no option to attack or defend against England. Whereas my 2 fleet builds can be used against England and are in position to do so.", "Cuz you did what I thought you were gonna do. I don't want you taking Belgium and I need you out of ruhr which is one of the places I thought you'd go and is kinda an aggressive move. Now I'm not super interested in giving up Belgium to be honest but I'm not an unreasonable man. Let's negotiate.", "At the end of the day I need a dot, whether that's Munich or Belgium or something else. In return I'd push fleets into Irish, English, and MAO, which sets up a convoy into Wales. And I might try to persuade Russia to help you keep Denmark.", 'On your end you should probably take the Helgoland Blight while you still can. That will make it especially hard for England to keep attacking you', "If the English fleet gets into Denmark and you aren't in the Helgoland, it becomes super easy for England to support themselves into hel and then convoy to Kiel,Holland,Belgium, etc.", 'But if you are in the Helgoland all of a sudden they have to support Denmark to hol', '"hold', "Alright I'll think about the move set and get back to you in the morning", "I don't see why you need a dot", 'Just disband the troop in ruhr. That would have us certainly on peaceful terms', "Because you're asking me to use 3 fleets, 1 army (for a convoy), and lose a unit to attack England. When you've been super aggressive towards me with your builds and moves. I'm not going to attack England if you aren't willing to make any consessions.", "OK I understand what you're saying. I'll think of something amicable for us both when I wake up fr", 'Did you think of anything? Just curious.', "Oh sorry. I've been real busy", 'Hold on', "I mean. One thought is to have me take Belgium this year and for me to give it to you back next year. That way you can build a fleet and I would be out of Ruhr as well (Ruhr to Belgium). And I'd use Belgium to convoy out", 'You still there?', 'Sorry', 'Yes', "No need to apologise. I get that you are busy for labor day weekend. Just know that I need a real response before the deadline is over if you are serious about actually working things out. I'll be around for the entire rest of the day.", 'I think that should be agreeable. Let me look at the map again', "Seems like you've lost interest in this game? I'd be upset if you weren't talking to me. But the truth is you aren't talking to anyone.", "If you've lost interest in the game you'll still get paid as long as you put in orders or until you get eliminated. I'd be happy to help you with either of those 🤣🤣🤣", "If you've lost interest in the game you'll still get paid as long as you put in orders or until you get eliminated. I'd be happy to help you with either of those 🤣🤣🤣", 'The west (you me England) needs to figure our shit out before the East comes and rapes us', 'Yeah I agree', "Sorry I haven't lost interest in the game it's just not on conspiracy so I don't think to periodically check this all", 'And the moves that got entered were from days ago', "So let's work something out. I'd love for us to stop all the infighting and make an efg happen", "That's what I wanted from the getgo", "Juggernauts coming though and regardless of if you are got buffer or not if you let that buffer go down in me and England it'll steam roll you just the same", "I'm thinking you want to move to Tyrolia and support Ruhr to Munich while I swing my fleets back south", 'Ouch, England got you good.', 'I can help you', "You still around? If you don't make a very specific move you will lose 4 supply centers this year. No matter what, you will be losing at least 2 supply centers. It's up to you how much you actually want to stay in the game.", 'How would like to work together though?', "Hold on and I'll respond more in full", "Yeah I'm still here", "Well, I'm not actually sure what the orders are going to end up being, but what I can tell you are my current moves so that it can help you plan your defense. I'm moving to Ruhr and supporting myself to Belgium (no use in lying about that). So Ruhr's support, whatever it is, will be cut.", 'I think it is safe to assume that Munich and Holland supports will also be cut', 'So my recommendation to you if you want to stay in the game would be to use Berlin to support Ruhr to Kiel.', "I tell you this with little risk since if you tell England, he'll simply change the plan to one without this key vulnerability", 'Now, you have reason to mistrust me, but the truth is that I have 3 fleets and only 2 armies. I stand to gain the least from continuing to attack you. And my largest concern is a Turkey/Russia or Austria/Turkey alliance, which is where I plan to put my focus. I intend to let England and Russia squabble over your supply centers while I move fleets south to help out Italy', 'And with Russia taking Munich, your survival means that we could coordinate to take it back in the case of a Russia/Turkey alliance.', 'So it looks like you really have given up', 'I know things are looking bleak, but if you are willing to entertain me for a bit I have a plan that might keep you alive, and thus get a slice of the $24 pool for survivors.', 'Just to make sure you see it- the plan would involve you retreating to Tyrolia and capturing an Austrian supply center', "Whatever the case, I highly encourage you to stick it out because that way you'll get paid", 'So.... ?']

messages:
["Hello, Russia! I hope we can both agree that peace between our nation's would be beneficial for the both of us?

I'd like to suggest that in return for letting me into Romania, you will have my support should you wish to expand into Scandinavia", "Hi Austria! I can definitely agree that peace between our nations would be good for both of us! Unfortunetly I can't agree to letting you have Rumania, as that is basically the back door into Russia. If you do try to take it, then there is going to have to be war between our two great countries. Also I don't see how you could really support me into Scandinavia... But that besides, I think we would both benifit from an alliance against Turkey. What do you think about that?", "In that case, I will keep out of Romania if you do the same, we'll keep it as a DMZ?

I'll admit my promise to help you with Scandinavia was a little optimistic, but do excuse me as I'll blame it on a tad too much Austrian beer.

We should keep an eye on Turkey, but I feel as though an alliance this early on will not leave us in the best of standing with the rest of Europe.", "If were going to have an alliance, we should aim for blitzing turkey. It's the power triangle; Austria/Turkey/Russia. Only one of them is going to survive very long. Also, what is your relationship with Italy looking like? Just a note: I am willing to work out an agreement of who gets what part of the balkans, but I am taking Romania. It is essentially part of Russia and leaving it as a DMZ just will not do if Turkey goes for the Black Sea", 'I will give you Romania as long as we can take out Turkey asap

Should we start this turn?', 'Ofc we should start this turn.', "I'll push down to Serbia and continue to push from the south", 'O.k. Can you trust Italy? How is your relationship with them?', 'I have not yet spoken in any great detail with Italy and am waiting to hear back from them', 'Alliance against turkey is still on right?', 'Of course. I heard back from Italy as well and we seem to be on the same wavelength', 'Why did you only move 2 units? Also turkey told me that u told him that I was going to attack you? What was that about?', "Don't believe Turkey, I said nothing of the sort. I imagine he's just trying to cause an upset between us.", '😭 that was mean', 'Oh well', "Awfully sorry, old chap. But all's fair in love and war", "I know you and turkey probably have a nice and cozy alliance right now. But despite your betrayal, I still think we could have a very powerful alliance that would be able to crush turkey within a year or two. If we got Italy  involved, I'm sure we could figure something out where, for example you support me into Rum, and Italy supports you into Bul.", "Hi austria. Turkey told me you're alliance is over. Is that true?", "It looks like you're alliance has ended. And before long, one of us in the east will be elliminated. I say we work together to make that someone be turkey", 'What do you think?', 'They told me they are interested in working with me against you and are going to try to take Ser. So what I think we should do is you attack Rum with Bud and Gal, which would cut support and let me take Sev. That way we get two of Turkeys territories, which would be a big blow to them', 'Do you have any proof to these claims?', 'At the same time however, it does seem plausible that Turkey will move on Serbia', "I'll do it", 'No proof... unless I took a screenshot ig... but I feel that goes against the spirit of the game', 'Good luck!', "No, I wouldn't expect you to take a screenshot, it's alright", 'Ok', 'If you can do Moscow S Sevastopol H and Galicia S Ukraine-Rumania this turn then we can most likely take Romania', 'Yeah. France told me about the orders you sent me', 'Thoughts?', 'I like them. Are you on board?', 'Aye', 'If this alliance works out(and I hope it does) we will have turkey dead pretty soon🙃', 'I stabbed you in the back once already, I owe you this one 😉', 'Thx', "Although technically, you're the one getting Rum 😩", "I've been short changed by Turkey, I need it at least for now 😅

Once we start pushing him back, you can take some of his cores", 'What are you plans for after Turkey?', 'Not sure yet... Italy maybe? What about you?', 'If i get a build, in the fall I can build a fleet in Sev to further our attack on turkey. What are you planning for moves?', "Do you think that maybe we should turn our attention to France? They'll be running away with it before long", 'Yes. we probably should', 'hey, any plans for this turn?', "ig ur prob going for bul, correct> Do you mind if I have RUM? I would support you  into bul from there if u did't get it this turn", 'or support u somewhere else if u did', "Hey, I'm assuming our alliance is over? I wanted to keep it going but didn't get anything from you.... If you want to I think furthering our alliance would still work, and I could help you fight france and also give u rum back(in exchange for helping me w/ turkey)", "Sorry, I've been swamped with work recently. France is our biggest threat at the moment and I think Turkey believes the same", 'Ok. So what do you want to do?', "I figure there's not much we can do to stop him from pushing in the north unless you're able to stop him from getting those SCs yourself. I'm pretty tied up in the South and reckon I'll be out soon enough. We just need to try and stop him slowly eating his way up to 18", 'Hey austria. Long time no see. Sorry for the stab earlier. I think we should try to work together to stop france from winning; if we work together we can stop france from getting 3 more centers, and then we will all win in a 3, 4, or 5 way draw when the game is hard-capped at 1910', "I know you probably don't want to work with me, but if you want for it to be a win (including you) then we should definitly work together", 'Vie, bud or ser moves to tri w/ the other two supporting', "Can bud and ser support me into tri, and I will give u ven next turn? I think that would be best since support can't be cut", 'Austria?????!!??', 'I really need an answer', 'Apologies for no response, I am in a different time zone 🙃']

messages: ['Hello Austria!', 'I believe we  may have shared interests on the eastern half of the map', 'I do believe you are correct', 'Hello!', "If you don't mind me asking, are you getting along with your neighbors?", 'I believe I am at the moment, apart from Russia that is...\n\nHow are you faring?', 'I am in quite the situation right now', "Being caught in the western triangle is not my cup of tea. That said, things aren't going too poorly"]

messages:
["Hey Austria! How's it going? I am hoping we can work together on this one. No point getting into any early conflict which will only serve to help everyone else. How do you like to split up the Balkans?", "Hi Turkey! I fully agree that we should stay peaceful with eachother. How do you like the sound of you getting Greece and Bulgaria and I'll go for Romania and Serbia?", "That sounds good. If we stick together we can get through this early game intact. What's your read on Russia and Italy? Have you heard from them?", "Haven't heard from either of them yet unfortunately", 'Ah well our biggest issue is keeping Russia out of Rumania. I will see if they have plans to move most units south. It sounds like they might be.', 'Russia is planning to take you out as soon as possible, and is asking me to help. How do you feel about moving against Russia, as I believe that he will be the biggest threat to the two of us. He is really posturing in his communications with me', 'Sure, that makes sense. Like I said, first thing would be  to keep Russia out of RUM, whether that be by supporting yours or my army in.  Italy is pretty quiet but what I did hear from him was fairly anti Austrian by the way. I believe they are probably pretty tight with Russia, them being natural allies anyway.', "Well I'm getting the same sort of stuff from Russia that you have. They are indicating to me that they will commit south and want to attack you directly with my help. I have told them I'd consider it but know that I am firmly locked in to working together with you. Looks like our neighbours have made the decision for us really which makes it easy right?", "I'm quite happy to support you going into Romania as I can imagine that I'll need my forces to fend off Italy. Will you be moving up to Bulgaria this turn and go onto Romania from there?", "Ok yes let's do that and I can support you into Greece the following year if you don't get it this year.", "Just confirming that you will support my BUL army into Rum this season? Looks like Russia is firmly committed South but Germany is gifting them Sweden and England looks like they wont put up any resistance either so we better not let them take RUM as well or they'll be running rampant in no time.", 'I can confirm that I will definitely be supporting you into Romania.

Russia has been trying to sow doubt between us by telling me that you told him that I plan to attack him', "Nicely done! I reckon we've got Russia on the backfoot now", "Yes, nice one. I'm glad we could sort things out. Next is to get you into Greece then we'll have secured our front and can go from there. Russia does have three on RUM but we can fend that off together and Warsaw for you and Moscow for me can be the mid-term goal. What do you think?", "Sounds like a plan. I'll support Rum this turn and move down into Greece", "Ah, I didn't see that Italy was in Greece. Would have been wise to check the map before sending messages", "Haha yeah well we can knock him out of there if you like, either in the spring or fall, he can't stop it since he built that fleet in rom...", 'What do you want me to do in regards to Russia?', "We can support your bud army into gal. I think that would be best. So I support you into gal and support ser army into Greece. If it works out for spring I mught be able to get a convoy in in fall but that's probably a next year thing.", 'Yeah okay, that works', 'Hmm we might need to change our plans. I think Russia is planning to go to sil anyway. Still on for Greece though. What are you going to do about tri? Can you trust Italy not to go for it?', 'Yeah i think best to support you into Greece in the fall. Just need to hold in rum this season. If you can still support me in rum that would be appreciated.', 'Roger that', "I'm not sure if going for Greece this turn is entirely preferable as Italy said they plan to move out and it might be better not to provoke them quite yet", 'Ok good call', 'Well looks like Italy messed it up. Anyway thanks for the support. Looks like I did need it after all. What do you want to do this season?', "Now Italy has moved into Tyr, which we agreed was a DMZ so if you could support Ser in Greece that'd be much appreciated. What do you want to do Vis a vis Russia?", 'No problem, I will support you into Greece. If you can attack gal to cut the support there and support me in rum that would be great. All going well we get one each. Do you think Italy will be getting out of Greece though anyway?', "Actually don't worry about supporting in rum, just the hit on gal should do it.", 'Just confirming that you still need my support into Greece? And can still hit gal for me?', 'Yes for both', "Italy claims to be moving out of Greece. I might need to pull the support. I'm being told that you and Russia might be attacking me instead 😟", "Meh I'll trust you over them. Ill keep the support locked in. If you and Russia wanted to take rum you could do it. Then we would be bogged down for the foreseeable future and that would just help the West. We have the jump on the west at this point so I'll hope you're still on board for that reason.", "Russia and I haven't been in contact since I first betrayed him. May I ask who told you this?", 'Italy was suggesting it more than saying it but they got me a bit paranoid anyway', "Now there's something. Italy was suggesting that he and I go against you", "Yeah I'm not surprised. He was also offering me support into Serbia. We can stick to our guns here and easily take Russia and Italy. Ive got the paranoia in check now.", "Aye, Russia was also asking me to turn on you but we've got a good thing going here", "Russia has asked me to work with him and Italy (don't know for sure that they are in cahoots yet), and suggested that he support me into Romania and Italy into Bulgaria. This is of course, not possible now that Italy had retreated from Greece.

I was wondering perhaps if I should string Russia along, so that we may know his moves?", 'You could definitely do that if you like. We will know more once we see where Russia builds', 'I suspect Italy and Russia would be working together at least at some level. They are obvious allies. We have the jump on both of them now though', 'So I was thinking I would push into UKR this year and then MOS. Depending on how things go, I can support you into WAR and go for MOS next year. IF you can support my RUM army to UKR and Russia covers WAR then the UKR army will have to disband. Also you can perhaps take the ADR? If you get it, we can get ION in the fall. What do you think?', 'Done and done. Supporting RUM - UKR, Disrupting BOH and hopefully taking ADR', 'What do you want to do for this one? We should probably repeat our fleet moves. This time we would get one or the other', "If you can disrupt UKR, I'll stop BOH and see if Germany could hit SIL and then I'll move GAL into WAR, which will deprive Russia of a build", 'Ok have locked that in', 'Might need to shift tack a little bit. Would love to break through into Russia but maybe we need to make ground into Italy first?', 'Aye, we seem to be in a bit of a stalemate at the moment', "Ill come in to the ADR so don't go there with your fleet. Also I will support your army in GAL to UKR - that might get us somewhere. But I guess we will have a new army in WAR to worry about. Will check again after the builds.", 'It wont be worth it. You just get to be the second target for Russia and Italy. If you want to turn it around, let me know', 'Although since Germany has given gifts to everyone and England has essentially stopped playing this game has deteriorated into pointless territory', 'It has gotten rather back and forth', "Well you've given up your best ally for... well... nothing? Are you going to follow through as Russia's Puppet?", "Honestly, at this point I don't even know. Fancied a little shake up as the game was getting a bit stale", "Yeah I get that. If you can convince Russia to worry about the main threat - France. Call a truce and you and I can both try and hold France back. If not, I will obviously just help France take it out for the price of my survival. I don't really mind either way", 'Will see what Russia has to say', "Russia should be moving to Boh and Sil, you and I should get into ION and TYS, knock Italy out because why not. However, if Russia doesn't move his armies west to Boh and SIL or he moves MOS to UKR, it will be pretty obvious that he's just going to take you out.", "I do reckon he'll try to come after me after I betrayed him at the start", 'If you want, I can support you into SEV. Up to you.', "And now there's support for you into Rum if you want it.", 'Aye, from Serbia if you could', 'Done', 'Reckon you could disrupt Romiana?', 'Yup, done', 'Ta']

messages:
['Hey Austria', "I wanted to ask if you knew about Italian intentions. I don't think he plans to move to Piedmont, which could be an indication that you want to play defensively.", 'I have not yet heard anything from Italy unfortunately.', 'What are your thoughts in terms of your moves?', 'Just looking to secure my borders at the moment. You?', "Yeah, I'm looking to secure my borders as well.", 'What are you thinking now?', '(In terms of working with Italy/Russia/Turkey)', "Naturally, I don't want to give too much away but I reckon you'll be able to tell soon enough", 'Very interesting moves', "You've done well getting 3 builds this season! May I ask if you have made any alliances?", "I have no chance of keeping Munich and England is in the channel, so it's honestly a less than ideal situation.", 'I was planning to work with Germany, but it seems like they plan to attack me now that I took Munich.', "Ah yes, that it's unfortunate", "So. What exactly is going on in your region? It looked like you and Turkey were buddies but those Turkish builds aren't that ideal for you I think.", 'I am very worried about a steamroller/Russia Turkey alliance', "I must admit that I am worried that Russia and Turkey are in cahoots, and Russia let us take Romania so that I'd trust Turkey for them to then turn on me and push West", "I think it's the most likely explanation for A Warsaw. If Russia was worried about Turkey, wouldn't they build A Moscow? Likewise, if Turkey intended to take Sevastopol. Wouldn't A Smyrna make more sense to capture Armenia and then Sev?", "I think it's the most likely explanation for A Warsaw. If Russia was worried about Turkey, wouldn't they build A Moscow? Likewise, if Turkey intended to take Sevastopol. Wouldn't A Smyrna make more sense to capture Armenia and then Sev?", "By the way. I was wondering for the longest time about you and Italy's moves. I won't tell anyone. But is the plan to convoy Venice to Tunis?", "That's freaking awesome if so", 'Not sure if it is the best plan if Russia and Turkey are working together. The army could be needed more in Albania', "By the way. Any suggestions for me in the north? I've been hearing different things from Germany and England so I'm at a bit of a crossroads in terms of who to trust and what to do.", 'Well, I found an ally since I think Russia will move to Silesia to pull some German units away from Munich', "I haven't heard from England or Germany on why they plan to do unfortunately", 'No worries. Hopefully you have things figured out with your neighbors. I think Turkey is sowing a lot of discord between Russia, you, and Italy to his own advantage', 'Aye, he is most likely up to something', 'You need a build this turn', "Whatever you do, don't let Turkey take Greece AND Sevastopol", 'Any updates on your plans regarding Turkey?', 'I will tell you this. In the first year, Russia told me he was working with you against Turkey. Somehow, when the orders were read, Turkey had convinced both you and Russia to work with him.', 'So it seems like Turkey has been playing both sides from the start.', "I'm not trying to be super nosy, and I apologize in advance if I am coming off that way, but for my long term interests it is pretty important that Turkey doesn't start explosively growing and wiping out half of the map. Any chance you and Russia can figure things out to recapture Rumania from Turkey?", "Russia won't work with me on this unfortunately", "That's too bad. Is it like he is not responding to you, or he flat out refused?", 'Because it is possible that he has been MIA for the past few days', 'Any Intel on England or Germany?', "England is worried about being caught in the middle of you and Germany. And Germany is just happy that we've tied up Russia", 'Cool- makes sense. It has been very quiet lately, which is concerning me greatly.', "I think that's just because it's the weekend. I imagine it'll pick back up once orders start going through", 'Russia was not responding due to the weekend and he said he would be extremely enthusiastic to work with you.', "Looks like you are in good shape. I'd watch out in case Turkey intends to stab you for 2 (Serbia and Greece)", 'So. What are your thoughts on this game right now?', 'Are you attacking Italy?', "I love to see you working with Russia against Turkey. I'm assuming a retreat to Ukraine with the idea of taking Rumania?", 'By the way, what is your plan with the Adriatic Sea? Will you be fighting Italy?', 'That was mainly to stop Turkey getting a foothold there', 'It might work in our favor actually if the plan is to dislodge Turkey from the Ionian- we have a total of 4 fleets to his 3.', 'Looks like:
Ukraine-Rumania
Moscow S Sevastopol H
Budapest S Serbia H
Serbia S Ukraine-Rumania
Galicia S Ukraine-Rumania

will guarantee you Rumania', 'What is your relationship with Italy like? I thought you two were fighting by bouncing in the Adriatic so much 😅', "I'm happy to help the cause and I've told Italy my moves each turn, but I still feel like I don't know what the plan is here. (Is there even a plan?)", 'Thoughts on moves?', 'This game is going very well for you. You have zero threats and allies all around you. You are highly likely to take Bulgaria and/or Greece this year', "We should talk about borders- if you can move your fleet from the Adriatic to Albania it would help you capture Greece, and I'd have no problems staying out of Tyrolia and Trieste if you are willing to do the same.", 'Thoughts?', 'Not sure why Italy disbanded Ionian, but I figure he may have missed the deadline for builds', 'We need to move quickly if we still want to get the edge on Turkey', 'Also, any thoughts on Russia?', "I'm fine with keeping out of Tyr and Tri to maintain a dmz between us

I'm not 100% sure about Russia at the moment, I feel as though as soon as Turkey is gone he will move against me", 'Sounds good. I agree, I would definitely not leave yourself open to being stabbedd by Russia if possible', 'It looks like you are aiming to take Venice? Meanwhile, Turkey has a walk into Tunis and will only get stronger. Maybe we should try to cooperate instead of fight?', 'What gives with the move to Trieste?', "Ngl, completely forgot about it being a dmz. I'm not attacking you dw", 'Ok- I can trust that since I think taking the Ionian and/or Albania is a priority for you', "Damn- I seriously did not intend to take Trieste. I had figured I would want to stay in Venice for the time being with you bordering it with two units and didn't think I would actually end up there", "If there is absolutely anything I can do to help you with my army in Trieste, it's your unit to order", 'I guess just pull back to Venice?', "Sure- especially if Italy keeps Piedmont, that might be the move. I am also happy to help support Budapest to hold so that you don't lose it to Russia. Speaking of which, I am assuming you are disbanding the Adriatic Sea? It doesn't seem to be very useful since Turkey will be able to keep it out of the Ionian anyway.", 'Any more thoughts now that builds have been put down?', "If you can support a hold in Budapest, could I take Venice for the time being? I'm getting rather weak as it goes", 'I feel like you should have kept Albania instead of Adriatic. Putting the fleet in Venice only moves us backwards', "I can't stop you from moving to Venice though I do feel like you are better off putting it on the front lines", "Disbanding Albania was a mistake, I'll admit", 'I was assuming a move like that meant you might be working with Turkey again, which would probably be a huge help for you', "Darn, we weren't on the same page last turn, but I'm super glad to see you work with Turkey again", "Russia is in a really good position to wipe you off the map so I would definitely try to slow him down. I'll do what I can in the North", 'Just as a sidenote, I noticed you held in Budapest, but it could have potentially supported Serbia to Rumania.', "Sorry, the bot was down for a short bit. If you support Budapest to hold with Serbia and Turkey cuts Rumania, you'll keep Budapest: otherwise you probably will lose it to Russia", 'Congrats on keeping Budapest!', 'We can definitely keep pushing back Russia', 'Turkey and Russia both told me that they want to eliminate you and England and go for a 3 way draw', "I'm not sure I'm very interested in that because we only just started making progress against Russia, and Russia/Turkey alliance is always scary and may be able to overpower me in the long run (they don't want to give me any of the builds)", "Would you be willing to support Tunis to the Ionian Sea in the Spring? Also, I can give you Trieste in the fall in exchange for Vienna if that's alright with you.", 'Oh crap, you have a disband', 'Not sure what the best disband is. Probably either Budapest or Adriatic', 'I think:
Budapest-Rumania
Serbia S Budapest-Rumania

 Gives you the highest chances of surviving from Russia/Turkey onslaught this turn', 'And actually, Serbia-Albania would ensure Turkey cannot outflank us', 'Darn, if you had moved Budapest to Rumania you would have kept Serbia 😩. GG', 'wait wait wait, you can retreat Serbia to Greece!', "If you retreat to Greece, I'll support you back into Serbia."]

messages:
['Hello Russia, I am curious as to whether or not you would be content to split Scandinavia equally between yourself, Germany, and me. Does that prospect interest you?', "Hi england! I'm assumimg that you're planning on heading to Nwy, and Germany would go to Denmark. If we could share that would be great! I would preffer if you went there with a fleet instead of a unit. I would be willing to give you unaposed access to Nwy if you agree to this (I won't move Mos-Stp, then Stp-Nor for a stand-off). Looking forwards to a great game with you!
-Russia", "Hey! That appears to be how things are going. I'll move my fleet into Nwy and we can have a grand ole time. Cheers and good luck!", 'You too!', 'Hey. Whats up with that anti - Russian start?', "Apologies. Not trying to counter you. I'll be taking Norway like I said but, and the other fleet is to pressure Benelux", "Ok. that's fair. It is a pretty typical opening now that  I think about it. As long as you don't convoy your army across, we should be good/", 'Thx for sharing! Good luck over there in the west!', 'My dearest Russia', 'I have a weird request', 'We share an Iberian ally, and that ally would love it if we took denmark this turn. Would you be willing to support SKA into denmark next turn? My Norway fleet will be heading south.', 'Rather took denmark next turn*', 'Ummm... ok?', "Lol I know it's weird. You can talk to France to verify", "Alright just a reminder to support Ska into Denmark so I don't bounce. I'm moving one of my fleets into Nor just because its not good form to leave an undefended supply center, but the denmark fleet will move west soon so we'll be back to one fleet each in the region", "I'm a bit confused here. I'm willing to help you take Denmark, but I am going to need something in return. I love the alliance between you me and France, but taking Denmark doesn't really benefit anybody but you. I would be willing to support you into Denmark, if  you move your fleet in the Norwegian west. I really don't like the look of all three of your fleets hovering over Scandinavia. If I support you into Denmark, and you move your fleet west, we will both have one troop in that area.", 'Alright. That works for me.', 'Is NWG to Edi good enough for you?', 'Yea, sure. Thanks for cooperating', 'Awesome no problem.', "Wait up. I'm assuming I'm supporting Ska into Denmark?", "I'm thinking of moving to Sil. If you could move into Hel, me, you, and franc could crush germany", 'Correct on supporting Ska.', 'I think our alliance with France has great potential.', 'and north to Helgoland?', "And I'm bouncing North Sea in EC but I am down to move there next turn", 'Also I agree with our triple alliance. That will be very helpful for everyone', 'Why would you bounce? Hel is a much more powerful postition', "I'm not exactly sure but France proposed it and I'm rolling with the flow", '?', "Sorry. I really am. I hope our alliance can maybe continue?? I was talking with France and a ton of the stuff didn't match up, and I was worried you would attack me. I should have let you know, as it is clear you only told the truth.", "What didn't match up?", 'Stuff like the bounce in English Channel', 'But what if I move out of Norway and let you get it back. Could that  save our alliance?', 'Ok, I need to go now, but we can talk in the morning?>', "Yeah let's talk then.", 'Hello. If you leave Nor this turn our alliance will survive for the time being.', "Again, sorry for the stab. In hindsight, I can't really say it was a mistake. Even though I feel bad I REALLY needed the build as Austria and Turkey are running a relentless attack against me. I appreciate you're cooperation. I fear if we go to war, I will be pressured from all sides and will be eliminated. But, that would probably also end the alliance with you and France, and they are looking in a much better position then you right now. So I would really like to continue our alliance. I will move out of Nwy this turn, provided you don't take Sweden.", 'If I have Norway and Denmark I am content.', 'Lovely. I have been talking to france, and in the interest of keeping you strong to fight Austria and Turkey, I surrender any german centers except Denmark to you', "I don't blame you for stabbing me, because it's reasonable to play aggressively if you think you're cornered. That said, my movements last turn ought to indicate that you're not cornered, so I am hoping we can return to normal relations. I am interested in the current FER alliance to counter AT and would prefer it survives.", 'Actually, I just looked at the map again. You can keep Nor for now.', "I'd rather you fight AT in the East rn, and it looks like you do need every single center you can get. I'll keep denmark but Nor is yours.", 'Wow', 'That’s really nice', 'Thank you!! 😊', "Np. Go show those silly south-eastern nations who's boss lmao", 'I love the spirit!', 'Is it ok with you if I move into Scandinavia>', 'What tile specifically?', 'Lol. I meant SKA', "I really hope you don't stab me. It would probably mean the end of both our nations.", "Nevermind. I won't move into Ska. Wouldn't be a good move anyways. Ideally I would move into Nth and you would move NTH to helgoland, where we could both attack Germany but I realize that you might not trust me enough to do that.", "I'm moving Edi into NTH, and NTH into helgo", "I won't stab you. If you're peaceful from here on out I'm chill to be peaceful like I have been", 'Ok. Are you ok with me moving to nth?', 'I will be peaceful. Would be in my best interests not to be anyways', "By nth you mean North Sea right? If so don't move there. My Edi Fleet is going into North Sea", 'To support south', "Yes, that's what I mean", "Won't move there then", 'Want me to support you from Edi to NTH?', 'nothing else for my fleet to do', 'Sure', "Here's a tentative plan for the fall: 
Kiel-Berlin 
Bohemia-Munich 
Silesia S Bohemia-Munich
 Burgundy-Ruhr
 English Channel S Picardy-Belgium
 Picardy-Belgium 
Helgoland-Holland 
North Sea S Helgoland-Holland", 'Enlands idea above', 'Alright thanks', "So I have a very weird proposition for you. What are your thoughts on me convoying an army into Livonia to help support you defending centers? I figure that France will hold the Med, so it's up to you and me to hold and push in the east.", "Idk... that seems like a very precarious position for me to be in if your army is in Livonia.... and although I would like this alliance to last a long time, we can't really know when/if our alliance will end and when it does if you have an army in liv...", "while I appreciate the offer I just don't think I can trust you with basically the fate of my country depending if you stab me or not", 'also just some intel I think Italy is a really bad player...', 'So what do you think about the future of this alliance? What happens when/if we are both large superpowers?', "That's fair on the Livonia idea lol. It sounded interesting but I'd probably decline too.", 'What makes you say that about Italy?', "And I am 1000% down to draw this out with FER, but if I get stabbed obviously I'm going to make it my life goal to be insanely inconvenient.", 'Hi. Can Kiel support Munich to Berlin? I would really appreciate it and would support you into a territory sometime', 'Sounds good homeslice', "Sweet! I'm just wondering about all your troops... where are they going to go? I feel like to only people you are in a good position to attack is me and France, which makes this sort of awkward 🙃", "Lmao I've been talking to France about that. Going to convoy to Italy and see the world a bit", "Stabbing either you or France would get me right solidly dead so I'm not looking to start a right", 'Lol how are you going to convoy to Italy???', "I believe you it's just you don't have enough fleets to get there. Trust me, I like this alliance too.", 'Just trying to figure out my plans', 'I know it sounds dumb 😂😂 France wants me to convoy via my and his fleets', 'Let me find what move he said he wanted hold up', 'He said he can move to EC and MAO to convoy me into North Africa', 'Lol ok', 'Alright how do you wanna split up Germany?', "Btw France doesn't want me to convoy anymore so I'm not sure what exactly the move is.", 'Ig u get Kiel and holland and I get Ber and Mun?', 'Sounds good to me', "Hey sorry about Berlin. France told me you reneged on something about Munich and I didn't want to piss them off. Hopefully we're still chill", "It's ok. Were good. Any plans for the next turn? You having 3 troops stuck in england really sucks...", "Yeah it blows lol. I guess I'm just gonna sit around. On the bright side side, even if I pushed out of mainland Europe I can just chill", "Here's hoping France decides it's time to do something", 'Hey partner. Is there a way to resolve our current disagreements without violence?', "Hey. I'm surrendering Kiel to you.", "Hi england; sorry I havn't gotten back to you. I'm really sorry I did that, and I feel kinda bad since I really like you as a player. You were in a really tough predicament there, with all you're troop builds, and nowhere to put them. And as much as would have loved to continue our alliance, you can see how tricky the predicament was. If the situation allows, I would be totally open to something in the future.", 'Good luck!', 'Thanks!', 'So out of curiosity... are you gonna try to take my home centers or can I just ride this one out?', 'Looks like france got me', "Lol it's kind of looking like that", 'yep', 'If you can survive  a few more years youll be in the draw', 'who knows', 'anything is possible', "That's what I'm hoping for😂I knew I wasn't good enough to win so I just wanted to hang out until the draw lmao", 'yea', "But I'm pretty confident I'll make it to 1910 and might be able to get a three way with france and turkey (sorry)", 'No need to apologize my man I respect the hustle. I hope you make it.', 'Thanks. I hope u do too', 'Loved our alliance while it lasted btw', "If you move Edi to North, and I support myself in norway, then france won't be able to take norway, and they will have one less center", 'Hey... could I ask a small favor of you?', "It's basically a lost fight but I'm not going to give up", 'England can you do that please?', "Hello comrade sorry about the delay class has been hectic. I'm down to go out in a blaze of glory I'll help you out", 'lol thanks 🥳', "Techically this if you were 100% self interested this would be gud for u 2 since france winning would mean there isn't a draw which you could be in 😤", '💯', 'Damn that was stupid of u', 'Oh well. Probably wouldn’t have mattered anyways']
