messages:
['Greetings from the South! Hope you are doing well! Wondering if we might be able to build a good relationship. Do you prefer to bounce in the black sea?', "Hey just replying to your message on backstabbr, happy to work together. So will you go to gal and ukr? I think we should still bounce in the black sea as it won't be great to make it obvious that we are working together...", 'Hi Turkey! I would love to have a good relationship between our two great countries! Are you up for blitzing Austria? Looking forwards to a great game with you! 
-Russia', "I think we should leave the Black Sea as a DMZ, as I would like to 100% ensure I get Rum and I'm worried about Austria taking it. So if we can agree to leave it as a DMZ I can move my fleet to rum", "Hmm ok that sounds fine,makes sense. As long as you're willing to help me take bud within the next couple of years and I'll return the favour for vie. What's your read on Italy in all of this?", 'He says that he and Austria have reached a truce for tyr', "Hey so I ended up going to the black sea defensively because of all the info I was getting from Austria that you were planning to attack me. Not sure whether you actually are or whether you had the same sort of information from them that I was planning against you. I'm hoping its the latter as we have a great opportunity to carve up Austria given their very passive start. They should only get one build so they will be behind.", 'Austria was telling me that you were going to attack me', 'Wait what?!?!', 'Austria is telling you imma attack you?', 'I agree w/ the great opportunity to get them', "Alright, well that just isn't true. I guess they want to try and keep us from becoming allies. How about this - you take Rum with support and I take the Black Sea. I get BLA for insurance and you get Rum which gives you an extra build. I will try for Greece and might get it then we will be set up to attack Austria", "To be honest, I don't really want you to have BLA. I'm just not there yet (although probably will be eventually). So what if I move to rum supporting myself, and you can attempt to trick Austria to support you into gre.", 'The ideal would be if I moved into Gal this turn, which would put tremendous pressure on Austria. But this would only work if my fleet moved too Rum, and you supported it.', 'If your working with Austria and betraying me I swear...', "Your basically for sure my ally now. Early in the game I was debating an alliance with Austria, but they seem to be spreading a lot of misinformation, and are asking for very unreasonable things. I think they still think I'm allied with them, so maybe I could persuade them not to move into rum and then you wouldn't even have to support me? If that worked it would be amazing as we would each get a build (I would actually get two).", "I'm spreading some rumors about me being allied with Austria, hoping the news get back to them so don't be alarmed if somebody says something about that to u", "OK I understand your hesitancy over BLA. Yes, Austria is spreading a lot of misinformation, to Italy as well as us. There are three things here and I can only give up one otherwise I'm putting myself under way too much risk. Its either 1) you taking RUM by yourself and I wont try and stop it 2) black sea DMZ (but we'd need to bounce it) 3) me supporting you into Rum. Whichever one you take, I can't give up any of the others. I would be too far onto the back foot with you getting a freebe in the North and Austria seemingly coming for me. 1902 will be a big year and if we work this out and we play it as allies then we can both have a lot of trust going into next year which will  be really valuable.", "I would really like a lot of trust between us, as our alliance can be insanely powerful. I'm going to take Rum, and PLEASE don't stop me. But you don't need to support me either. I don't see why you would want BLA if not  too attack me?", 'Oh man', 'Well played Ig.', '😭', "Ah very difficult to work out what was going to happen there after the first season. I knew I had to at least not give up the Black sea as that would be terrible for me. I had to protect it. It doesn't mean we have to be in all out war though. I just got too paranoid I guess.", 'Mhm.', 'Right', 'obviously I can totally trust you, right?', "I'm willing to be allies with you", 'But I just can't believe that you were "protecting yourself" by moving to the black see. And as for your message before, 1 and 2 are just normal things that we would do in an alliance, those don't harm you at all." 1) you taking RUM by yourself and I wont try and stop it 2) black sea DMZ (but we'd need to bounce it) 3) me supporting you into Rum. "', "ok. So how about I won't attack you in Rum, if you don't attack me in gal. does that sound fair?", 'That sounds fair to me.', "Oh it seems I didn't send that message off. I guess that's why you went ahead and attacked me in rum", 'I think a move into Eas could have a lot of potential.', 'For me?', 'Oops. I meant Greece. So ig ur going to attack me in Sev. Last chance to crush Austria?', "Ok yes let's do it. I think they are after me anyway", "I'll support you into bud", 'Great. I will support you into Sur next turn then', 'lol turkey', "I did not have enough time to change my orders. Plus I didn't know which army to support... We needed more time.", 'Ok. Try again next turn', 'I think I will move Moscow into War, with Sil supporting, where I could go for Austria the following turn.', 'Also I will move Ukraine to gal. Could you support me there?', 'This is where we need to trust each other. I will be leaving Mos undefended and I need you not to stab me', "Sorry, got all this way too late. I really have no idea whether you're actually willing to work with me or not at this point but I am open to ideas.", "I would like to work with you. I realize that you and Austria have an alliance against me, but so far you guys haven't done that much(although I will admit you have me anoyed 😤). Right now, you could lie to me, tell Austria your plans, and stab me, but I think that the better option for both of us is to work together against Austria. It seems like they totally trust you, and have left many territories undefended. Currently me and Italy have an alliance, and together the 3 of us could rip through Austrias territory, as they aren't expecting it", 'If you are up for this, I think the ideal attack would be:
Aeg - Gre
Ion s Aeg - Gre
Rum - Ser
Bul s Rum - Ser
Con - Bul
Sev - Rum', 'This would garuntee you two of Austria supply centers, unless Austria does something very weird.  I could support myself into Gal, and attempt to move for Vie.', 'So, what do you think? Up for leaving you Austrian ally behind and siding with me? Our alliance, if it works, could be a monumental one', 'You still around?', 'Im up for this if you can confirm - so you want to take back Sev though right?', 'And is Italy on board?', 'Italy is on board.', 'I would like to have sev back, yes. I would be willing to give you support sometime in a future turn if you let me have sev back.', 'I would almost think that you are controlling Austria and turkey', 'Your absolutely ridiculous.', 'You have such a good chance to stab Austria, and your practically doing nothing against me.', 'And I think I have lost count of how many times you have stabbed me', "I was honestly ready this time. I thought we had more time. I needed more time to sort it out with Italy. I see they didn't support me so luckily I didn't get the moves changed.", 'Mhm', 'You’ve only said that, oh, how many times?', "If I don't hear from you, then lets leave this until next year. I need confirmation otherwise its too risky.", "I told you I needed confirmation otherwise it was too risky. I didn't get confirmation from Italy and there you go, too risky wouldn't have worked.", 'And you tell me Italy is on board and next minute they are asking me to support them into Greece', "Ok fine. You didn't really do any damage to me anyways", 'But now we have the whole weekend to work this out.', "And ultimatly, I don't really care anymore what you do'", "but if you attack me again I won't be up for negation anymore", "OK but I can't give up SEV, not yet anyway. Way too dangerous. Move into GAL and I'll support you into BUD in the fall", 'You're funny. Why is giving up Sev "way too dangerous? It's not like me having it gives me access to very much of your territory... it is Russian territory after all. You are already a very powerful country, and if you do as I suggest, moving into Gre and Serbia, you could have nine supply centers. If you give me Sev, I will support you into Bud', 'So I think the ideal would be something like:
Ion - Gre
Aeg s Ion - Gre
Rum - Ser
Bul s Rum - ser
Sev - Rum', "Sev is too dangerous because Sev to Arm together with your ally Italy by sea and its basically and I just lost Austria as an ally. In the short-term then you have 3 to attack RUM with. Also, you think I can hold off you, Italy and Austria at the same time? I don't, not without SEV and not after giving up the ION as you're suggesting. Also, why would I be giving up ION in this scenario anyway if not to allow your ally Italy to come back at me by sea. And I don't know where you get 9 from? 6 + 2 - 1 = 7 then you're really going to support me into RUM in the fall *as well* as the 2 I got from Austria? So you get 1 and I get 3, that's really the deal you're happy with? Still totals to 8 by the way but we both know you have no intention of supporting me into RUM in the Fall. You will be attacking RUM with 3 while Italy tries to push through by sea. It doesn't take a genius to see that. Next time try and suggest a deal that actually has some appearance of sincerity otherwise it's just too easy to see through.", "Well... that was harsh. Let me just put a few things straight. Me and Italy is not a thing. I communicated with them the first year about a potential mid game alliance, as I didn't want to be the only one fighting you and Austria. But if you look at their moves, we haven't really done any work together. We haven't even communicated in years. If you look at what they have done so far, you'll see that they are a.) a very bad player or/and b.) are not at all committed to the game. They have basically communicated with nobody, haven't really attacked anyone, and had a good amount of invalid orders. At this point it doesn't make any sense for me to communicate with Italy, since they are a bad player and are going downhill fast. An alliance with you would be much better.", "If what you say about you and Austria not having an alliance anymore is true, then it looks like you don't have any friends at all close to you. And I know you're feeling very strong right now, but you will lose all of that if you don't have a powerful alliance. We are both strong countries, and a war would basically mean both of us getting put out of the game", "For the record, I don't think you can hold off me, Austria, and Italy at the same time. Definitely not. And although I have no interest in an alliance with Austria, they will be my second option if you continue to be this bellicose.", 'Also can you read? I never suggested Sev to Arm, nor did I ever say I would support you into Rum. Make sure you get the facts straight before you go on a rant like that.', "And one last thing. If everything happened like I said we should do it, you would have 8; 6 + 1(serbia) + 1(greece) + 1(bulgaria) -1(sev). But that doesn't mean I only get one. Have you noticed my units in Munich and Silesia by any chance? I think you were overreacting.", 'So, I'm still up for an alliance. I think it would be in both of our best interests, and could be very powerful" But you need to stop constantly saying shit like"oh we never really worked it out" or "oh, I'm sorry it was too close to the adjudication period", and then completely running over my ideas as soon as I say them. Sure, they weren't 100% ideal, or truthful. But we can talk, and work out the kinks instead of you going on this rant about how bad and unrealistic the plans are.', "I know you didn't say anything about sev to arm, that's your army I'm talking about having the potential to move there but more likely you just attack rum. And yeah I meant your offer to support me into bud not rum. That's what you said you would do but I can't beleive you would do that so don't include  it in the offer.", 'ok, probably true', "But you can't know that lol", 'So ummm.... do you want to try to make something worK?', 'Sure', 'Watch me trust you and get burnt. Looking forward to it', "I'll back off and attack Italy and you attack austria", "Can't give up sev though but you'll probably be able to take it anyway.", 'Lol actually I was thinking "watch me you and get burnt"', 'Great minds think allike I gues', 'So what are our short term plans? I still strongly think you should take Serbia', "Also, just letting you know, I'm telling austria that I'm going to attack you and that I want to make an alliance to attack you, just thought I would let you know. Ofc it isn't true, I'm just trying ot get them to move where I want", "I'll just support myself in sev and rum which means you can take gal", "Army StP? Good luck with that one 🙂 We had a chance vs France but you and Austria don't. I'll have the black sea this year and i'll be the Turkish Turtle for the rest of the game 👍", "LOL. Some of you're own medicine turkey. I just can't believe how many times you said you would do something and then you didn't... Why would me and you have a better chance against france than me and austria?  And havn't you noticed my alliance... Well, good luck turkey. I can't see us doing anything together for the rest of the game if I'm going to be completely honest.", "Did you see my moves last season? They were exactly as I said. Thanks though, good luck to you too. You've got a good chance now to win! 😃", "Ok, now that I look at the moves again ig u didn't do anything you didn't say you would. But you didn't do anything that would benifit us, lke going for serbia or gre. Whatever, doesn't matter now. And who knows, if a miricle happened you could turn this game around and win it too!", "Hey, france is getting huge. I'm not suggesting an alliance as it appears nothing works against us, but maybe we could set some of our disputes to allow us to focus our energy on trying to prevent france from winning?", 'If you give me berlin back, I can support you into edi', 'I will happily do everything in my power to get you Berlin back :)', "WOW. I couldn't tell you how much that means to me!", "Lol but I would like to prevent France from winning. Can't do much though from where I am.", 'Yeh. taking med tho', 'Would b good', 'Would be great if I could. I agree.', 'I think you will be able to. U have 4 fleets and france only has 3', 'I will do my best', 'Gl', 'Realistically, nobody is going to be able to win before 1910, except maybe france has a tiny chance? Anyways, I know that we mutually have absolutly no trust for eachother but I think the most strategic  option right now is to put our differences aside and elliminate austria + england and go for the 3 way win', 'Remember, the game is hardcapped 1910', 'So france has shown a lot of interest with me trying to get me u and them to go for the 3 way, which I think is a good idea... but if u do want to go for it we will have to be on the lookout because there is a good chance france is lieng and is going to try to go for the solo', "France is on 15. They have won this game easily. He only needs three more. He could even do it this year. Nap, Lon at least. Get an army into the UK and next year will be done very easily. He was also telling me the same thing but if he doesn't go for the win he's crazy. I'll lock in 3 way draw no problem but this game will be over next year with a French win no matter what we do.", 'eh', 'If austria works with me we can basically take a center from france this turn', 'I think we might be able to do', 'it', 'No other options, really,', 'SO I say we keep talking to france about plans for our 3-way, but then work out something with austria and go against our word to try to draw it', "There arn't really any other options", 'Sure, happy to do whatever. Throw everything at France because, really, its our duty not to just give in. Die fighting. Can you support Ser into Tri? I wont make any play for Sev. I should have built another fleet. That was dumb.', "Or get him to support you into tri. I wont cut any. Then you can give him Vie back. 1 for 1. I'll just lose Nap and keep that fleet in Apu to help vs Ven.", 'yeh, just wainting on a message from austria so we can coordinate', "Alright, let me know what you want me to do - I'm just locking in Gre to Alb to help with Tri in the Fall if needed. Holding everywhere else.", "shouldn't we eliminate austria? This wouldn't harm us; in fact we would get our troops up there to fight france, and it would be a 3 or 4 way win instead of a 4 or 5 way w", "let me know if i'm wrong", 'this is just me thinking how to stop france', '?', 'Hellooo?', "I don't think so. Better with all of us vs France. But wither way France wins so whatever you like.", 'K', 'Austria isn’t responding which is rly a problem', "I'll support gal into bud then", "Let me know if that's cool", 'Ok. Put that in your orders. But if I get a message from Austria saying they want me to support them to try I won’t move into bud, so be prepared for a last-minute message', "It reallys sucks we didn't get a hand on austria... with them we definitly could have taken tri", 'U know what', 'lets let them have tri this spring', 'its still the spring', 'so u take serbia from them, and I support myself into bud', 'that way it wont seem like im betrahing france, and we are ready to take tri next turn', 'Is taht good?', 'Oh god were running close to the deadline', 'Btw if u betray me I will just be baffled at how self interested you are', 'NOt that I think u will', 'U there?', 'Sorry for all the messages', "Alright I'll change my order", 'k', 'do u like the plan?', 'Sure, would be good to be in tri in the spring though so we can put pressure on ven but stick to that. Destroy Austria.', "Hmm you didn't move out of Bla and against france? Ig I understand why u completly dont trust me but I feel that was a poor decision", "Do you seriously think it would make any difference at all? I'm honestly asking. This game has been over for 2 seasons at least. It doesn't matter what we do now. Do you see the freebies in England? Who might be able to take those? Its first to 18 and France is on 15. Good on you for fighting to the end, but this game is over!", 'eh', 'Keep trying', "Turkey: 
A Ser - Tri
F Alb S Ser - Tri
F Bla - Con
A Rum - Ser
A  Bul S Rum - Ser
Apu - Ven
Ion - Nap
Russia:
Bud S Alb - Tri
Gal S Vie H
Vie H
Nwy H
Nwg S Nwy H
War - Pru
Ukr - Mos

England:
Edi - Nth

This garuntees us Tri, and prevents france from getting any centers. I think these are basically the best possible thing we could do in this situation. Please don't give up. Give it your all till the very end", 'No problem. Will check those and enter them later today.', 'k great', "Ahh you have Bud S Alb to Tri but I think I'm taking Tri with Ser? I think Ser is best so support that in there?", 'Ok I’ll support that', 'That’s what I meant the whole time but typo my bad', 'But yeah do everything as the above except for bud supporting ser to tri']

messages:
["I'd love to work with you this game- not sure what your thoughts are, but in my opinion Russia and France are the two countries who are the most natural allies on the board", 'Hi France! I completely agree with you - Russia and France really are great allies. For now we might not have to much to do with eachother, but I would love to have an alliance with you! How is it looking in the north? Are you thinking of teaming up with England or germany? I would recommend england as an ally, as I have heard rumours of germany trying to takey you out. Looking forwards to a great game!

-Russia', 'Sounds great! I took your advice and am working things out with England. Hopefully we can keep things balanced between them and meet up somewhere in the middle.', 'Them being England and Germany', 'Any thoughts on your south? A Russia/Turkey alliance could work well since I think that Austria and Italy may be fighting early on.', 'Hmm. Do you know any more info about that?', 'Unfortunately not, Turkey has been unwilling to share their plans', 'Hmm. Are you still allied with England? They did a pretty anti - Russian move there.', "I think England's moves might actually lean more pro Russia given that the army move failed and England will have to put a fleet in Norway. An army in Norway would be a lot more anti-Russian for sure.", 'That being said I am trying to see if England would be interested in making some anti-German moves which can help get England off of your back', "What's the scoop regarding Turkey/Austria? Looks like everyone made relatively conservative openings", "I'm with Austria. Going for turkey", "Umm. Well, that's not good", 'Why is that?', 'Obviously not anymore though', 'It looks like Austria helped Turkey against you, and Turkey stabbed you', 'I was actually allies with them both and was going to stab Austria but ig not', 'Yeah', "I wonder if attacking Turkey with Austria is still on the table given Italy's position to help with Bulgaria and/or Rumania. Italy has a highly vested interest in seeing you do well too.", 'Have you and England talked at all about taking Denmark from Germany?', "Turkey's builds are looking pretty good for you", 'Hopefully you both made up?', "I'm not sure if me and turkey are allies anymore... If you want, you could clear the order with turkey, and move munich into Tyr, where you could help take Austria out.", 'Sure, if I have a retreat I definitely plan to move there', "By the way I've been spreading misinformation by saying that you will move to Silesia (just thought I'd give you a heads up)", "Darn, it looks like Turkey is really committed to attacking you which is too bad. Is Austria willing to work with you? This might be the best chance you both have of taking Rumania so I've strongly suggested to Austria that they support Galicia to Rumania.

I figure that cutting Rumania support is the best chance you have of keeping Sev, though Turkey has it guaranteed if they simply cut Ukraine support.", 'By the way, what are your thoughts regarding what you plan to do with Sweden?', 'Are you willing to work with Austria?', 'You there still?', 'Do you have information on German or English plans? Some Intel would really help at this point', 'Hi france. I just got back from a long weekend, but now I will always be here ☺️. England wants me to attack Germany in Denmark, and said that you had requested that. Is that true? No idea about Germany as they are not responing', "Italy seems like they are messing up a lot. They had 3 invalid orders, so I don't know how strong of an ally they might be", 'What about you? Got any intel?', "I would love to work together with Austria, as I think it would be a very powerful alliance. But I fear I can't stop turkey and Austria from continuing to attack me. Also I'm a little worried about England 😰.", 'Hmm. I was under the impression that England would attack Denmark and that he wanted you to support him into Denmark.', 'Yes. But did you request that?', 'Sorry mistyped above. I meant England moving into denmark.', 'Well, I assumed England would do it anyway because it should be a guaranteed supply center. England and I have been talking a lot', "I think if you move to Norway you'll be better off, I didn't ask England to get you to support him I don't think but I did ask England to move to Denmark (otherwise I'd worry what else those fleets are up to)", "Yes. Me and England are on pretty good terms as well, but I really hope they don't attack me. What do you think the likelihood of that is? I think later in the game an alliance between me, you, and England could be insanly powerful.", 'My hope is that England supports himself into Denmark', 'True', 'True', "Hmm. It's honestly really tough to read England. I don't think they are going after you but they did mention taking Sweden earlier int he game so I might request a bounce in Norway or something like that", "So you think I should move to nwy? And do you think I should arrange a bounce or use it to stab. I don't really want to attack England", "Hmm. If you don't really want to attack England I would arrange a bounce probably. I don't know what Norwegian Sea is up to but it is probably best if it stays there", "There isn't a ton of time before the deadline so I'm not sure if England is online or not", 'I told England to move from nwg to Edinburgh and they agreed in return for me support a move to denmark', 'How close are you with England?', 'Sweet. That works fine as long as England follows through', "Also rn I don't have any things I need w/ Warsaw. Anywhere you would like me to move it?", 'I feel like if everything works out our alliance could last a long time and has potential to become very powerful.', "I don't actually think I'm that close to England right now, but we talk a lot. He's said he will help me against Germany and I am somewhat skeptical of whether he will follow through or not", "I don't thing Germany has many friends 💀", 'If I move to Silesia with war, I could help you w/ germany', "I'd love to see that honestly", 'Alright. Hopefully in return for support I could have Berlin and you would get the rest of Germany?', "Especially if the three of us work things out, you could drop down to the Baltic Sea and we'd be able to split Germany very quickly", 'That sounds good to me', 'Right. But things might not work out that great if I move into Nwy.', 'Haha', "I'm kinda worried about attacking England, since that would mean England, Austria, and turkey all going after me and I don't think I can handle that.", 'Yeah', "I need to go, but I'll be back in 10  min if you wana keep talking 😁", 'Sounds good', "Here's a thought. If we're taking down Germany, it would make sense for you to support England to Denmark", 'And then England moves North Sea to Helgoland, Norwegian Sea to North Sea, and Skaggerak to Denmark', 'Unfortunately it seems that England is not online', 'Do you know which unit England wanted to move to Denmark with?', "Yea I don't want to attack England. I think I will support instead.", "Perfect. I agree with your decision. After a brief convo with England I'm a lot less concerned about things because enow the stories are all matching up", 'Soo... you did just talk to England, correct. Cuz I just messaged them and they are for sure online', 'Yep I did talk to them. I think they were having connection issues earlier which is why I thought they were offline', 'they say they are bouncing North Sea in EC', 'Checks out. We organized a bounce rhere', 'Wait by EC do you mean the English Channel?', 'Yep', 'Sorry about me moving into Norway. I was pretty worried they would attack me and some things didn’t match up. Also I really needed the build. Now I feel bad cuz they we’re completely honest 😭. Hopefully England will accept my apology and we can continue our alliance?', 'Honestly the build was worth it I think. Asutria and Turkey are seriously strong together and stopping them will be a lot harder than I first thought', 'Yes. Thx for understanding.', 'Turkey is crazy. They try to make a deal with me and they betray every time. Austria won’t respond to my messages. And basically nobody can help me over there. So hopefully I will be able to hold them off and get some extra builds from Germany', 'I wish Italy was a better player then they could help', 'Anyways I need to go to bed now but talk in the morning', 'Omfg turkey is ridiculous.', 'They just said “ i did not have enough time to change my orders. Alliance still on”', 'Imma play gullible and just go with it 😂', 'God', 'Sorry for the all the messages', 'Yeah they are def lying lol 😂', "Building Warsaw and Moscow I'm assuming?", 'Oh crap, you retreated to Bohemia?', "As much as I love to see you in Bohemia, I worry you won't be able todefend your Homeland effectively", 'Do you have relations with either rturkey or Austria?', "What's the deal with Norway?", "England says the alliance might work if I move out of nwy, which I probably will, since I can't have another enemy. Turkey thinks I am very gullible, and keeps saying we will attack Austria, but he is 100% lying. Austria won't respond to my press. I messed up with that retreat. Imma build in Moscow", 'Damn', 'They r letting me keep NWY', 'Let’s hope It’s not a stab, but I don’t think it is', 'We should coordinate orders. I think Germany plans to take Burgundy so I am currently defending it and imagine any supports it gives will be cut.', "Can Bohemia head to Munich to cut Munich support though? I want to get clever and see if I can get away with this move but it relies on Munich's support being cut.", "Also do you have any reads on England? I could move into Ska but only if I'm sure they won't attack", 'Sure. Do you want me to go as for as to support my move into Munich, or do you think Sil should head back to War instead?', 'Oops. Not SKA. Nvm', 'HellO?', 'Hey', "Not a good read on England right now. But he told me he wouldn't attack you if that helps", 'I would not move Silesia to Warsaw because you want to make sure Ukraine has a valid retreat option', "I don't think a supported move on Munich will work right now, but that's what I'd lean towards unless you want to do a tactical pull back with Moscow-Livonia Ukraine-Moscow and silesia-Warsaw", 'Nah', 'silesia could also go to Galicia', 'To cut support and hopefully keep Ukraine', "rn I'm having Moscow to sev", 'with Ukraine supporting', 'sil to gal', 'boh to mun', 'Sounds pretty good', "I'm pretending to be in an alliance with turkey and I told them I was moving out of Moscow into Warsaw, so hopefully they will take the bait and move there instead of to gal", 'True', "Here's a tentative plan for the fall:
Kiel-Berlin
Bohemia-Munich
Silesia S Bohemia-Munich
Burgundy-Ruhr
English Channel S Picardy-Belgium
Picardy-Belgium
Helgoland-Holland
North Sea S Helgoland-Holland", 'This guarantees you Munich (unless something weird like Austria moves Galicia to Silesia??).', 'It guarantees England Holland and guarantees me Belgium. And England already has Kiel.', 'Basically, Germany loses 4 dots in one turb', "And if Ukraine goes to Warsaw, I think you'll be well defended and can build (since you are picking up munich) in St Petersburg. This way, you'll be able to defend Warsaw and Moscow too", 'Thoughts? There may be room for refinements.', 'Sorry, gtg to bed. Talk in morning', "Any new thoughts so we don't run too close to the deadline again 😅", 'Yeh I agree. I like your plan.', 'And Ig mos would just move to sev?', 'bwahahahaha', "I'm trying to get turkey to work with me. If they actually do that would be AMAZING as first we could crush Austria and then I could stab them", 'Moscow to Sev makes sense', 'It would be great if Turkey did that! Though I worry Turkey might not go for that as my communication this year with him made it seem like Turkey was not interested in stabbing Austria.', 'I sent England the orders u sent me btw', "yea. All they have done this game is stab me, so I would be suprised if they actually did't lie this time.", 'I feel like turkey might be on board... we’ll see soon. If he is, Austria will lose two supply centers. If he’s not, I should be ok', 'Nice!!! Had we known about the German NMR, we could have eliminated him this turn. That being said, this is still good.', 'What are you thinking for builds? It depends on how you feel about England, but if you can trust them then A Warsaw would make sense', "Rn I'm just laughing  at Austria and turkey", "Turkey had such a good chance to stab Austria, he could have gotten two of their territories and put them out of the game, but instead he continues his war with Austria against me and they can't even capture any territories 😂.", "Idk about England so far they have been completely honest but they just asked me if they could convoy one of their armies into Livonia so they could help help defend my centers but I don't think I trust them enough for that", 'Yeah haha, I think you might even have the chance to retake Sebastopol next year at this rate', "On second thought, you might need the unit in Livonia honestly. It looks like Austria is intent on taking Bohemia, supporting themselves to Silesia, to then cut Warsaw support to take Ukraine, and then take Moscow. It's a 3 season maneuver, but it honestly is what is going to happen.", "I just asked Turkey why he isn't stabbing Austria. He replied that he is playing to solo. So I guess his thought is that he'll keep Austria as a puppet for the entire game and hopefully eek out enough progress to then brutally stab Austria on the last turn.", 'With these kinds of players, you kind of have to just hunker down and form coalitions to fight against them... and honestly the only reason it is working is Italy is just letting them make so much progress in the Med.', 'I am having trouble keeping in contact with Italy, but what I want to do is work with him closely in the Med and put up a lot of fleet pressure in the south.', 'If you can get in touch with Italy, it would be awesome to try and convince him to help with that', 'k', 'We should start planning our moves', 'Also what are you thinking for the future of our alliance?', 'For sure. It does depend a little bit on English builds, but I honestly think that for the short term future we should be applying pressure on Austria and Turkey until they are forced to fight each-other.', "On my side, I'll be trying to work with Italy. If Italy remains uncooperative, I may have to move to attack them.", 'What are your thoughts though?', 'I am pretty confident that Austria will support Bohemia to Silesia. For that reason, I recommend:
Warsaw S Silesia H 
Munich-Berlin
Kiel S Munich-Berlin
Burgundy-Munich', "I'll send this to England as well", 'Thoughts?', 'The safest way would be something like this:
Warsaw S Ukraine
Moscow S Ukraine
Munich S Silesia', 'New thought:
Ukraine-Sevastopol
Moscow S Ukraine-Sevastopol
Warsaw-Galicia
Silesia S Warsaw-Galicia
Munich-Berlin
Kiel S Munich-Berlin
Burgundy-Munich

This move set has all of the advantages of both move sets', "Ok, I'm here now. I know I have said this every time, but I think I might have something with turkey", "We are working stuff out rn. They said they arn't in an alliance with austria anymore which, based off last turns moves, is totally plausible.", "Also, what do you think about turkey? If you have looked at their moves throughout this games and their alliances (basically none) it seems evident that either they arn't very committed to the game, or they are just bad at it. I have communicated with them a few times, but they don't really seem interested in talking.", "I like you're moves. Although would Burgundy to munich be permanant? Or just moving through?", 'Also I think you should go to war with Italy. They are weak, play bad, and are getting closed in on from all sides(if you attack them). Try not to let turkey get all their territories and become to strong 😅', 'I was thinking that, I am waiting for replies from Italy and England first though.', 'ok', 'Think I should try to play austria and turkey against eachother for Rum so I am garunteed to get it (if austria attacks)?', "I am looking to get another build soon to get another fleet on Italy, so as long as you were taking Berlin, and it looks like you aren't in immediate trouble, it would make sense to make the trade as I feel it is a bit more natural. But it's a bit to early to definitively say", 'If you can get them to fight that would be ideal, but I am 99% sure Turkey is lying', 'how so?', "I'm paraphrasing, but Turkey told me he was not going to attack Austria because he wants to eliminate you first", 'oof', 'ok', 'So is England on board w/ Munich to Berlin?', "Also did you see england's builds? Given their position they are most likely going to turn on one of us and recruit the other to help out pretty soon...", "They don't really have anyone to attack but me or you", "Also I would really preffer you not move into Munich. There is a good chance I won't get Berlin anyways if england doesn't support", "I haven't heard back on the support to Berlin yet unfortunately so it might be best to operate on the assumption it will not happen for now", 'I am currently not moving to Munich, but let me know if England talks to you', 'Ok', 'Heard anything from England?', "You're right, they probably intend to attack one of us. The builds make it ambiguous to who they plan to fight.", 'If they do, should we work together too take them out? The builds of only troops imply a convoy, so I think it would wipe most of their opportunities if we took out NTH... but then again, they might not attack us', 'I can support Norway to North Sea', 'But I agree with your analysis that they want to convoy out, so taking North Sea would definitely slow them down a lot', 'So do you want me to move to the North Sea? They are saying that they are going to convoy to Italy but that seems implausible...', "Up to you, I'm happy to hold", 'Ok sure, let’s wait one more turn. So for England has been true to their word, so..', 'Sounds good', 'Nice job getting Austria to turn on Turkey!', "So, just by the board position we have two options.
1. Take Holland and North Sea from England this turn. I would bounce Italy out of Munich and you would get a build, presumably a fleet in St Petersburg.
2. We don't attack England since he's been a very reliable ally, and commit fully to the attack on Italy and Turkey. This would look like sending all of my fleets south, so it would mean losing the option to efficiently attack England later, and also potentially leave us open to being stabbed by England.", 'Any thoughts or suggestions?', "Regarding the Austrian retreat from Galicia, I think it makes sense to retreat to Ukraine and take Rumania from Ukraine. That way, Turkey won't be able to retreat Rumania to Ukraine.", "I sent this to Austria as a recommendation and thought I'd share with you too:
Ukraine-Rumania
Moscow S Sevastopol H
Budapest S Serbia H
Serbia S Ukraine-Rumania
Galicia S Ukraine-Rumania", 'Silesia-Warsaw is necessary as well I think in case Austria stabs you', "I don't really want to turn on England... but we could", "They told me you told them you didn't want to convoy their troops, and they said they didn't know what to do with them", 'So what are we doing about munich', '??', 'France... I need a response to get my orders in. If you see this in time please move one(w/o) support unit to Munich. Then you might bounce Italy but you might get it which would be ok to ig', 'Sorry for the late response', 'I was thinking that in order for my armies to be useful, I inevitably need to be moving through Munich to get to Tyrolia and other key territories anyway, so it seems more natural to me to have Munich and for you to have Berlin. There is also the fact that I kind of need a build right now, so if we are not attacking England I would like to have Munich as you are already picking up Berlin and Sevastopol.', 'Awesome- looks like you have one supply center open for building in St Petersburg and one build, which works out perfectly.', 'We need to get you a build this year so you can put a fleet in Sevastopol', 'Wow you got lucky... got one of my territories and two of Italy’s...', 'If we’re going to abandon our English ally, I’ll build a fleet... but if not, prob an army', 'So... England, or no?', "It's now or never, I say we should go for it", "I have to say though, I really like England as a player, so it's a lot tougher of a call than I'm letting on.", 'I think though that you could get away with building an army and moving it to Finland, as to not set off any warning signs. Finland has a lot of advantages including the ability to defend both Sweden and Norway', 'So I would probably build an army in St Petersburg even if you are on board with attacking England', 'I also do want to wait for builds since I actually might not be able to even attack England due to Italy, Austria, and Turkey hating my guts', 'How are things with Austria? Hearing anything interesting lately?', 'Intial thoughts:
Moscow-Sevastopol
Sevastopol-Ukraine
Galicia-Bohemia
Warsaw-Galicia

This achieves a strong position to corner Italy as well as potentially bounces with Armenia, allowing you to build F Sevastopol in the winter', 'Anti English:
Norway-North Sea
Berlin-Kiel
Munich S Berlin-Kiel
Ruhr-Holland
Belgium S Ruhr-Holland
English Channel S Norway-North Sea', 'This accomplishes the goal of getting you a build in Kiel, and takes the North Sea, Holland, and Belgium all in one turn.', "If you'd like, we can probably wait to make this move in the fall so that England will immediately have to pull two units off the board for builds", "I'm up for doing it this turn. Or next. I will also move Stp to Finla d", "Sounds good- let's wait a turn then", 'Ok. I will still move to finland this turn ig. Hopefuly that doesn't send off any alarms to england, though it probably will. but I can say something like "it doesn't really have anywhere else to go, and it's just for safety seeing as you attacked berlin last turn"... or something along those lines', "So, if I'm going to be completly honest here(something that doesn't often happen in this game 🙃), I'm a little bit worried about you getting a few more supply centres and running off with the game. You took Munich from me, and then also two of italys. Nine supply centres and a good position. A little bit disturbing, if you can understand. And no, this doens't mean I'm calling off our alliance, or teaming up with enland,(that would be stupid of me as they are completely stranded).  So we are both strong countries, and could probably get away with a two way win, but are you at all interested in that?", 'True. If we do it right, a fall stab should be unpreventable even if England does suspect something.', 'I appreciate you bringing up concerns: I would definitely be interested in a two-way win. It might be comforting to know that the supply center gap is absolutely temporary as Italy and Austria will work together to push me out of both Rome and Naples (not to mention, the fact that it ties up 4-5 of my units just to the Italian front). That on top of getting you a build this year should even things out, if not put things in your favor.', "Yea. Too early to tell about a lot of this stuff. Here's to a good alliance🥂!", 'We should both keep talking to england; maybe suggest some orders that would make our attack more effective', "True. Just to be safe, it would be a good idea to dislodge the north Sea and prevent any convoys. It's going to mean England will know what's up, but I think our attack is unstoppable anyway. I think I can do this with just Belgium and English Channel", 'It might be smart to move Norway-Sweden and St Petersburg-Norway in order to try and make a play for Denmark too next year', 'Oh man I wish I could have seen that in time so we could have coordinated...', 'Oh well', 'No worries', 'I am supporting Berlin to Kiel so absolutely make sure Sevastopol is open for a fleet build (probably Moscow-Sevastopol and Ukraine-Sevastopol). Also try not to let Turkey find out, because otherwise he might try to support you into Sev', 'Any thoughts on what you want to do with Norway?', "Ok sounds good. Nwy will move to Ska maybe to take denmark, since you are already big and it wouldn't really make sense for you to have it after this turn(so take it this turn and I'll take it back and support u somewhere else instead) if thats ok with yo", 'Sounds good regarding moving to Skag. We can definitely organize a way to split up English supply centers, though I am a bit cautious of doing it now since I expect to be losing supply centers in the short term (to Austria).', 'So you moved to the North Sea. What gives?', "Yeah last minute I decided that was a better position, since one of us should probalby occupy it, and it also has access to denmark. I hope that's ok and doesn't come accross as agressive. I will totally move out of there next turn if u ask me too, since you have more fleets that need to get out into the sea", 'But I think that turn went amazing; I got rum from austria, and bounced in sev. Looks like you did pretty well too. I think if we continue this alliance, we could totally win', "I think I will go with an army in warsaw, instead of a fleet in Stp, since I broke off the relationship with austria, and england doesn't seem like a threat. IS that good with you or would you preffer me to build in Stp, to get Enland out of the game quickly?", 'Cool- we might be better off with you in the North Sea actually since it opens up the option to convoy to the island next turn. It depends somewhat on English disbands. Warsaw is fine with me- I agree with your logic, and we probably have enough units for England anyway', 'Great! Thanks mate', "You didn't build a fleet in Sevastopol?", "The weak point in England's defense is Edinburgh so we should try to find a way to take that", 'Oh god I messed up.', 'Forgot to build', 'It happens sometimes. I think you still have a strong position in the south unless Turkey and Austria start working together again', 'Thoughts on sending north Sea to Norwegian Sea? I worry that a convoy is easily distrupted but Edinburgh is easy to take if we do that', 'Any ideas for Trieste?', "How is a convoy easily disrupted? You realize that one has to dislodge a unit in order to stop it from convoying. And france can't do that. Although Ig they could stay in edi, but moving to the norwegian wouldn't change anything about that", "If you're there we can plan our moves", 'I can keep kiel and berlin, right? Since you got the rest of germany. So w/ my unit in kiel maybe i should go to denmark? Or i could do that with sweden', 'Triest could support me into venice?', "Do you want me to convoy one of you're units to edi?", 'Although me moving to venice is pretty risky, if austrai and turkey team up', 'You could say something to austrai about an alliance to try to get them not too attack you', 'sorry for all the messages lol', 'How about this:
A Gal - Vie
A Kie
A Mos - Sev
F NTH
A Rum
A Swe - Den
A Ukr S Rum
A War - Gal

A Tri - Ser
A Hol - Edi', 'Because England will move Wales to Yorkshire and thus there is no way to convoy to the island', 'NTH-Norwegian Sea IMO so that I can move my fleet to the North Sea but everything else seems ok', "ok. Any suggestions? So i'm assuming you will move to serbia?", 'W/ my fleet in nrth sea i will support you into england if you do me that favor', 'also ig kiel will just chill?', 'I think I have to defend Venice from Austria but I will try to get Austria to make some bad moves', 'I think it makes sense to hold in Kiel', 'Maybe move it back to Berlin or something', "I could move to Serbia it just means I'll lose Venice and Trieste too and Edinburgh is unfortunately not guaranteed, so I think I'd have to keep Denmark in that scenario to avoid losing 3 supply centers in one turn", "That's not entirly fair... chances are you will loose either venice OR triest", 'And when im in viena i can help u into bud', "So how about we go with what I said, and I don't take denmark this turn but I will take it next turn(or maybe not) depending on what u have for supply centrs", 'idk what do u think would be best for both of us on the whole', 'That works for me', "k. I won't move to denmark this turn then", "I really hope you don't betray me as I think that would be bad for both of us in the long run and if we stick together we are basicaly garunteed a win at this point, but if we fight it could escalate and we would destroy eachother", 'lol', 'I agree- betraying at this point would be short-sighted. In many ways, you are better positioned to stab me than I am to stab you since I have so many units tied up in Italy, Austria, and Turkey.', "Well, i can't say I agree with the latter, but I agree with your first point 😘", 'lol france', 'i sorta knew u would do that but I wanted to give u a chance', 'I have to be honest I’m pretty disappointed about that', '😭', 'Ig I overestimated', "I know what this looks like, and I think you should make whichever moves make you more comfortable, but I needed to find a way to convince Austria to work with me against Turkey in the fall and split them up, so as a condition I put in these moves. That being said, it's a spring move, and so my plan is to reverse the spring by walking back out of Kiel and Berlin", 'I have to say that the Austrian moves were an unexpected and great surprise, as it will be putting massive strains on Turkey and Austria working together in the long run.', 'If anything, you have a build in pocket, and are picking up Vienna and Budapest.  If I was going to stab you I would have chosen a different turn and told Austria about you moving to Vienna', "LOL nice try France. If your going to try to persuade me that taking two of my centers isn't betraying me, then I don't know what too say. And why in the world would you need Austria to work with you against turkey? You're overrunning the map, and turkey is probably the least of your concern right now. If you didn't want this too be a betrayal, you could have told me and worked something out beforehand. And yes, I have a build(s) on my hand, but unless you actually do as you say, and move out of my centers, I won't really have a chance for winning. I could have gotten you in Denmark, and although I considered it I didn't.", 'But if you do want to work something out and move out of my centers that would be pretty nice ...😁', "I mean, you will definitely be in the draw if that's what you meant. I would have 100% proposed this beforehand, but I felt that the plan might be jeapordized if you weren't fully on board. I get that you feel like you have to move to defend yourself and in that sense it unfortunately makes sense for me to hold onto Kiel and Berlin since I expect to be losing 2 supply centers in the south, and it seems like you aren't interested in supporting North Sea to Edinburgh.", 'Turkey is a cunning player and I fear that with the right tactical positioning Turkey would be able to conquer the Mediterranean，especially since I only have 3 fleets to his 4, and considering the superior defensive and offensive position of Turkey on the map in regards to naval power.', 'you keep saying your going to lose centers and you never do... your probably going to take munich...', "You say you didn't stab me but you are bieng completly unreasonable in everything that you are saying.", 'In this (not losing centers) I truly have been extraordinarily lucky, but it is bound to end at some point.', "Well you can't know that.", 'So what do you want to do', '16 min to figure this out', "It's just highly unlikely, but I guess it is still theoretically possible for me to continue growing this turn. Next turn it is impossible as I will no longer be bordering any supply centers that I can possibly take", "So i'm assuming you're going to take munich?", 'ANd your unwilling to give me berlin or kiel back?', "My pitch would be eliminating Italy, Austria, and England and going for a 3-way draw with Turkey since at this point we can't eliminate Turkey by 1910. Not sure what your relationship with Turkey is like?", "I'm open to the possibility of giving back either and/or not taking Munich. I think it makes sense for me to keep them unless we can figure out a deal with Edinburgh", 'Also england might be difficult to get down quickly unless we get builds as fleets and send them over there which kind of feels like a waste', "OH god, don't get me started on turkey. They are really hard to agree with. But that is the most likely outcome. Although if you get a few more centers from austria and stab me u will win.", "It's not likely when I'm still on 12, but yeah the other alternative is to keep either England or Austria alive and settle for a 4 way draw", "If you want me to trust you I think you should give at least one back, as you are much bigger and frankly it's probably in your best interest to go for the solo, although if the rest of the contries cooperate you almost certaintly won't get it. And your definitly going to need me if you want to go for the draw", 'But no lets not do 4 way', '|f your going to give me one back I think it would make most sense if I had berlin, but you would most likely move berlin to Pru or Sil which is scary even in the most trusting relationship', "That's fair. I agree, the difference between 3 way and 4 way is pretty significant.", 'I think a three way is probably possible', 'Should I message turkey', 'Sure', "Do you know anything about Austria's moves?", "Unless you give me back/let me keep one of them, I don't think I will agree to bieng your ally, and this game will probably end in a 5 way draw hard cap", 'No idea about austria', 'So berlin will move to silesia', '?', 'Ahh', '1 minute', "That's a reasonable position to take- I can give you one back for sure. Though maybe it makes more sense to support you to Edinburgh for a similar effect and not having me move to Silesia?", 'ok we have one min change ur orders', 'no time to work out something for edi', 'lol this is stressful', 'next time we need to work out something before this close to adjudication', "Damn! I changed my orders but they didn't go through for some reason", 'Shit', 'Yeah that was cutting it way to close', "I don't know if I can believe you but now were fucked", 'this is really bad', 'lost rum', "and didn't get bud", 'That was extremely unlucky in the south, Turkey and Austria guessed completely correctly somehow', 'ANd wow ur working with turkey?', 'Ok I need to go]', 'Tmrow maybe we can try to work out a 3 way draw', "Hmm. More like the move mutually benefits us as it means he isn't in the Gulf of Lyons and also means Italy is eliminated", 'yeh ig', "Alright, we'll talk tomorrow for sure", 'Alhtough tbh u might be able to get the solo', 'If you go for it gl', "The south did go very lucky for me last turn, but I don't think the dots that I need are within reach for at least a couple years- thanks though lol", 'So the *best way* to go for the 3 way draw right now would be for me to move North Sea to Yorkshire and move Skaggerak to North Sea while you convoyed an army from Norway into Clyde. This way, we can take both London and Edinburgh in the fall, and next year I would support you to Liverpool', 'In the south you can easily take Serbia and Budapest provided that you can actually work with Turket', 'What are you thinking for builds? It would kind of make sense to build against England, but if you are worried about me expanding I would be ok with an army in Warsaw', 'We could convoy Norway to Clyde. Or, if you prefer, I can support Norwegian Sea to Edi', 'Did you work out a plan with Turkey?', 'Ok i;m here', "messaged turkey, but they havn't responded yet", 'Ok lets do a convoy into clyde', "Sorry, didn't get a chance to respond to this. I wish you did the convoy, since at least then you could have gotten Edinburgh.", 'Turkey made a large oversight in the 3-way draw plans by letting Austria survive and retreat to Greece', "I mean, I really didn't expect you to keep to your work", 'It only made sense you would go for the solo', 'Your probably going to win but I wont give up 😤', "Fair enough. I made some lucky guesses in the south, but I'm pretty sure you have me stopped. I have a 3 way draw set, so it will really depend on how fast England gets eliminated.", 'Idk... I think youll win. Only need 3 centers and u have like 3 yrs', 'Yea tbh u got insanely lucky', 'and ur a good player', "We'll see- my luck has to run out at some point ;). Interesting to see that Turkey still doesn't quite trust you as he stayed in the Black Sea instead of moving it to Constantinople and against me"]

messages: ['Hello Turkey. I believe we could benefit from coordination as it relates to the East. Are you open to some level of dialogue on that issue?', 'Hello! I am certainly open to this and welcome the opportunity. How goes diplomacy with your neighbours?', 'Hello! That is wonderful. Diplomacy with my neighbors has been thus far lovely. How goes yours?', 'All pretty civil if a little quiet at this point down in the corner here.', 'Well one thing I can tell you is that Russia is indicating that they are committing south. Thought you might be interested in that :)', 'Awesome thanks!', 'Hello Turkey! Thank you for what seems to be accurate intel! I am curious as to how you and Austria are getting along?', "Things are up in the air as far as I'm concerned! I don't know what they're up to. I think Russia has benefited most from the opening season. I would be concerned about letting them get too much up North"]
